INSERT INTO `djangocms_text_ckeditor_text` VALUES (4,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) is one of the four inaugural schools of ShanghaiTech University. SIST\'s mission is to cultivate, nurture, educate, and train future technology innovators, enterprise leaders, R&amp;D specialists, and entrepreneurs in information science and technology. The SIST integrates world-leading scientific research environment with life-enriching and transformative education experience for our students.<br>\n<br>\nThe Schools cutting-edge research activities are designed to address global and national strategic challenges and needs of information science and technology. The School promotes both basic and applied research of the highest level by recruiting world-class scholars and researchers with international reputation as faculty members to establish state-of-the-art core technology laboratories, by collaborating broadly and closely with world-leading universities, research institutions, and hi-tech companies, and by taking advantages of Yangtze Deltas vibrant eco-environment rich with academic talents, financial strength, hi-tech industrial base, and superb regional economic policies. SIST is committed to undertaking and support national key R&amp;D projects, with strong aspiration for scientific and technological breakthroughs. SIST has the clear objective of becoming a regional, national, and international development workhorse by directly contributing to global technological advances with creative ideas and disruptive innovations. <br>\n<br>\nThe School emphasizes the establishment of an innovative and personalized education system for our undergraduate and post-graduate students. Our curriculum centers on individual academic supervision in all educational processes and learning activities. We promote an innovative and modernized educational experience to keep pace with rapidly evolving R&amp;D areas of information science and technology. In doing so, SIST can provide personalized teaching and training programs for students of various interests, backgrounds, and needs. The School continues to deliver a cutting-edge curriculum that consists of practical/advanced courses, exchange programs and internship opportunities with world-leading universities, research institutions, and hi-tech companies. We also offer special joint degree programs with international partner universities. By integrating teaching (campus), research (laboratory), and practice (company), SIST is proud of its competitive graduates who exhibit balanced characteristics of vision, ethics, responsibility, leadership, creativity, and entrepreneurship.</p>\n\n<h3><strong>Main Research Areas:</strong></h3>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p>1) Electrical Engineering</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Analog and Digital Circuits, Power Electronics and Systems, Intelligent Machines &amp; Robotics.</li>\n <li>Signal Processing, Information Theory, Communications Networks, Control Theory and Systems.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>2) Computer Engineering</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Architecture, Compiler, Operating Systems, Software Engineering</li>\n  <li>Multi-core and Parallel Computing, Computer Networks, High Performance Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>3) Computer Science</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Computation Theory, Algorithms, Database</li>\n <li>Machine Learning, Artificial Intelligence, Big Data and Cloud Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>4) Computing &amp; Mathematical Science</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Optimization, Numerical Analysis, Applied Statistics, Distributed and Parallel Computing.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>5) Interdisciplinary Information Technology</p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Bioinformatics, Bioengineering, &amp; Biomedical Engineering (with SLST).</li>\n  <li>Microelectronics, devices, &amp; optics (with SPST)</li>\n  <li>Sensor Networks and Cyber-Physical Systems (with SPST, SEM)</li>\n  <li>Renewable Energy Technology (with SPST)</li>\n  <li>Social Networks and Applications (with SEM)</li>\n  <li>Quantum Computing and Next Generation Computing (with SPST, SLST)</li>\n</ul>\n'),(10,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) at ShanghaiTech University will lead the charge in China\'s higher education reform by becoming a top academic research institution that is home to world-class research laboratories and faculty members. The School\'s Mission is to create a unique open and free academic environment that enables all researchers young and senior to achieve their full academic potentials.  The School will serve as the cradle that trains future scientists,  engineers, entrepreneurs, and industrial leaders in information sciences and technologies to play key roles in the ongoing economic transformation of China and the world.  </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><img id=\"plugin_obj_18\" title=\"Picture - sist-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(12,'<p>Welcome to the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, a place full of academic passion and research expertise.</p>\n\n<p>As you surf through our website, I believe that you will find a team of world-class faculty members, a group of creative and hardworking students, and many research areas that are well connected with domestic and international IT fields. Please join us in witnessing how ShanghaiTech is to become one of the best research institutes in the world.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><img id=\"plugin_obj_22\" title=\"Picture - dean.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" alt=\"Picture\"></p>\n'),(14,'<p><strong>Faculty Search Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a>, <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=329\"><u>Zhi Ding</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Faculty candidate screening, interview, and recommendation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Staff Search Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Academic and administrative personnel search and recruiting.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Academic Affairs (SAA) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Graduate and Undergraduate Programs.</li>\n <li>Degree requirements and petitions.</li>\n <li>Academic conduct regulations.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Curriculum and Teaching Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=132\"><u>Hao Chen</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>Course planning and new course approval.</li>\n <li>Undergraduate student advising and mentor program.</li>\n <li>Graduate student advising.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Graduate Recruitment and Admissions (GRA) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=8\"><u>Pingqiang Zhou</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Graduate admission policies, procedures, and decisions.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>SAcademic Seminar (SAS) Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=6\"><u>Ziyu Shao</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Organizing and hosting SIST seminars and distinguished lectures.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Public Relation and Collaboration Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=209\"><u>Youyi Zheng</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n <li>International and industrial collaboration.</li>\n  <li>SIST webpage management, newsletters Production.</li>\n <li>Public relation and societal outreach.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Research Developing and Planning Committee</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Chair：<a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=3\"><u>Yi Ma</u></a></strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Responsibilities：</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Research developing and planning.</li>\n  <li>Lab equipment planning and budget.</li>\n <li>Research and lab management.</li>\n</ul>\n'),(28,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) at ShanghaiTech University will lead the charge in China\'s higher education reform by becoming a top academic research institution that is home to world-class research laboratories and faculty members. The School\'s Mission is to create a unique open and free academic environment that enables all researchers young and senior to achieve their full academic potentials.  The School will serve as the cradle that trains future scientists,  engineers, entrepreneurs, and industrial leaders in information sciences and technologies to play key roles in the ongoing economic transformation of China and the world.</p>\n'),(30,'<p>信息科学与技术学院（School of Information Science and Technology）致力于聚集和成就未来信息科学领域的学术大师，培养和团结信息技术及相关应用领域的创新人才和创业领袖，力争在信息科学与技术的重点领域取得突破性和前沿性的创新成果，实现新科学和新技术的快速转化和产业化，孕育并服务于信息通信领域的国际领军高科技企业。 </p>\n'),(31,'<p>信息科学与技术学院（School of Information Science and Technology）致力于聚集和成就未来信息科学领域的学术大师，培养和团结信息技术及相关应用领域的创新人才和创业领袖，力争在信息科学与技术的重点领域取得突破性和前沿性的创新成果，实现新科学和新技术的快速转化和产业化，孕育并服务于信息通信领域的国际领军高科技企业。 </p>\n'),(32,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(33,'<p>信息科学与技术学院（School of Information Science and Technology）致力于聚集和成就未来信息科学领域的学术大师，培养和团结信息技术及相关应用领域的创新人才和创业领袖，力争在信息科学与技术的重点领域取得突破性和前沿性的创新成果，实现新科学和新技术的快速转化和产业化，孕育并服务于信息通信领域的国际领军高科技企业。 <br>\n<br>\n本学院的科研工作将面向全球重大挑战和国家战略需求，充分发挥长三角地区在人才、资金、科技产业和政策等方面的优势，吸引和聚集一批具有国际声誉的学术带头人来建立国际领先的关键技术研究实验室，通过与国内外顶尖大学、科研机构和高科技企业通力协作，掌握并引导国际信息科技的发展趋势，集中力量攻克核心技术难题，踊跃承担和支撑国家重大科研任务。 <br>\n<br>\n本学院的教学工作将采用导师负责制，面向最前沿、最尖端的信息科技研究领域及其迅猛发展趋势，积极开展与国际顶尖大学、科研机构和高科技企业的合作与交流，为学生提供个性化教学和培养计划，开设先进实用的专业课程，提供国际合作的本硕双学位计划，强化结合实际的企业实习和社会实践活动，注重培养学生的国际视野、团队精神、领导才能、创新和创业能力。 <br>\n<br>\n本学院将以我们的毕业生之科技和创新成就为荣耀和成功标志，真正成为科学领导者、技术创新者与未来革新企业创办者的乐园和摇篮。</p>\n'),(35,'<p>上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院（SIST）将投身国家高等教育改革创新事业，立志成为一个拥有世界级科研实验室和教授团队的顶级学术科研机构。信息学院致力于营造一个开放、自由、独立的学术氛围，支持和激励学院每一位科研人员最大限度地将自身学术潜能转化为令人瞩目的科研成就。信息学院致力于成为信息科学与技术领域未来科学家、工程师、创业者和产业领军人物的摇篮，为中国乃至世界的经济转型和发展做出关键性的贡献。</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_38\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - sist-1_nb3zhrv.jpg\"></p>\n'),(43,'<p>欢迎各位来到上海科技大学－信息科学与技术学院！</p>\n\n<p>在您浏览我们的网页时，相信您会发现，这是一个充满学术热情与科研专业的团队。这里有世界一流的师资，有积极向上资质聪颖的学生，有国内外一流的信息技术和尖端的科研项目。我非常希望有机会与您一同见证，上海科技大学成为全球首屈一指的高校的成长过程，更欢迎您对于信息科学与技术学院的成长给与关注和支持。欢迎您的到来！</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_44\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - dean_tLoNDas.jpg\"></p>\n'),(45,'<p><strong>师资招聘委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u>马毅</u></a>、<a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=302\" target=\"_blank\"><u>丁峙</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>学院教授推荐、招聘及考核。</p>\n\n<p><strong>职员招聘委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u>马毅</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>教辅、行政人员招聘。</p>\n\n<p><strong>学术委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u>马毅</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>本科生和研究生的培养方案、学位要求、学业管理以及学生学术规范等。</p>\n\n<p><strong>教学指导委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=11\" target=\"_blank\"><u>陈浩</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>本科生和研究生每学年的课程设置及教学安排、新课程及教案审核、研究生教学指导以及本科生导师管理等。</p>\n\n<p><strong>研究生招录委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=6\" target=\"_blank\"><u>周平强</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>研究生招生政策的制定、宣传和招录工作。</p>\n\n<p><strong>学术讲座委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=5\" target=\"_blank\"><u>邵子瑜</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>学院学术讲座的组织、安排和接待。</p>\n\n<p><strong>国际交流委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=93\" target=\"_blank\"><u>郑友怡</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>国际交流合作，学院网页、学院Newsletter的编制和管理及其他相关宣传工作。</p>\n\n<p><strong>科研发展规划委员会</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>主席：</strong><a href=\"http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/cn/StaffDetail.asp?id=2\" target=\"_blank\"><u>马毅</u></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>职责：</strong>学术研究的发展和规划，实验室设备的预算和规划，学术研究和实验室的管理。</p>\n'),(50,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(52,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(54,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(65,'<p>10月29日，上海科技大学与加州大学伯克利分校签订合作备忘录，双方协定在今后五年内开展教育、文化和科研合作。签约仪式在中国科学院上海浦东科技园举行，中国科学院上海分院院长江绵恒与加州大学伯克利分校校长Robert J. Birgeneau共同签署了合作备忘录。中科院上海浦东科技园建设总指挥华仁长、上海市教委副主任印杰、威盛/HTC集团董事长王雪红、中科院院士饶子和、中科院上海高等研究院筹建组组长封松林、上海科技大学国际合作负责人龚晋慷以及加州大学伯克利分校工程学院副院长Tsu-Jae King Liu,分管外事的副校长Scott Biddy、助理副校长David Jeu及其他相关人员参加了签字仪式。<br>\n　　<br>\n上海科技大学与加州大学伯克利分校协议商定将在今后五年开展教育、文化及科研合作。作为教育合作的启动项目，加州大学伯克利校区工学院电气工程与计算机科学系将会与上海科技大学共享部分核心课程的教学资源、相关材料和在线课件。针对每门课程，上海科技大学都将派遣教师前往加州大学伯克利分校学习教学和研究方法。<br>\n　　<br>\n此次合作备忘录的签署是上海科技大学开展高水平国际合作的一个重要举措，旨在进一步推进大学的国际化进程及学科建设，深化开放合作的办学思想，建设领先的科教信息交流平台，实现高水平的科研和教学活动。<br>\n　　<br>\n加州大学伯克利分校是美国顶尖的公立研究型大学，为社会输送了大量人才。秉承教学、科研和公共参与相结合的办学思想，加州大学伯克利分校以其悠久的历史和优异的教学质量成为世界顶尖大学。</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_66\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_67\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_68\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1.jpg\"></p>\n'),(73,'<p>October 29, 2012: Today, ShanghaiTech and the University of California, Berkeley signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to launch a collaboration in education, culture, and scientific research over the next five years. The signing ceremony was held at Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS). Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, and Dr. Robert J. Birgeneau, Chancellor of the University of California, Berkeley, signed the MoU. Dr. Renchang Hua, Chief Commander of Pudong Science and Technology Park, Dr. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, Ms. Cher Wang, Chairperson of VIA/HTC Group, Dr. Zihe Rao, Academician of CAS, Dr. Songlin Feng, President of the Shanghai Advanced Research Institute, CAS (SARI) and Dr. Jinkang Gong, Principal of International Affairs of ShanghaiTech University attended the ceremony along with delegates from UC Berkeley including Dr. Tsu-Jae King Liu, Electrical Engineering Division Chair and Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences Associate Chair, College of Engineering, Mr. Scott Biddy, Vice Chancellor for University Relations, Mr. David Jeu, Assistant Vice Chancellor for International Relations, as well as other staff with the delegation.<br>\n<br>\nShanghaiTech and UC Berkeley have agreed to be in partnership in education, culture and scientific research over the next five years. As a start to the education collaboration program, faculty in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences in the UC Berkeley College of Engineering, will share some of their core course instruction resources and instructional materials and references with a selection of courseware being developed for online format. For each course, ShanghaiTech University will send faculty members to UC Berkeley to learn their counterpart faculty member’s pedagogical and and research methodology.<br>\n<br>\nThe MoU signed between ShanghaiTech University and UC Berkeley represents a significant move for ShanghaiTech in promoting high-level international collaboration to boost disciplinary development and deepen its educational vision of sharing and openness in order to be a globally recognized research university.<br>\n<br>\nThe University of California, Berkeley serves as a world’s premier public research university. It is recognized as a major source of future talent. With the mission of teaching, research, and public service, UC Berkeley has earned its top ranking and global reputation through its time-honored history and outstanding academic achievements.</p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_74\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_75\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\"></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_76\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\"></p>\n'),(81,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(83,'<p align=\"left\">ShanghaiTech University recently hosted a highly successful 2012 Frontiers of Information Science and Technology (FIST-2012) Workshop. FIST-2012 took place from December 9-13, 2012 at Parkyard Hotel, Zhangjiang Hi-tech Park, Pudong New Area, Shanghai. This high-level international workshop is initiated and organized by the School of Information Science and Technology. FIST-2012 workshop is one of a series of technical events during the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University. <br>\n<br>\nFIST-2012 invited over 60 major speakers from around the world, a large number of which are world-class senior researchers, professors and industrial experts. Focusing on the future development of scientific research and education in information science and technology, these distinguished speakers presented their recent exciting research findings, discussed important technological progresses, and articulated their visions on future research directions. More than 200 workshop participants took part in this unprecedented meeting of world class IT experts, covering a wide spectrum of frontier topics from big data, computer vision, to sub-millimeter wave imaging. FIST-2012 also invited Professor David Tse of UC Berkeley and IBM’s Dr. David Carmel to deliver two plenary lectures titled “The Science of Information: from Communications to DNA Sequencing” and “IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge”, respectively. The plenary lectures stimulated a high level of attention and exciting discussions among workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_94\"></p>\n\n<p>Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, delivered the opening lecture titled “Urbanization, Industrialization, and Informationization” during the opening ceremony. Following the progress and modernization of society through, urbanization, industrialization, and the recent informationization, Dr. Jiang delineated the general development trend of society through information revolution and globalization. He further emphasized the necessity, importance, and urgency for China and China’s education system to break through traps and stagnation experienced earlier by nations in similar stage of development and modernization. Dr. Jiang introduced the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University as the government’s response and commitment to confront these difficult challenges. </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_95\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, presented the founding principles, the planning, and the current progress of ShanghaiTech University in his major speech on behalf of the ShanghaiTech University Steering Committee.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_96\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Zhi Ding of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) served as the chair of the workshop and the opening ceremony. On behalf of Dean Cher Wang and the SIST team, he articulated the founding principles and future plan of SIST in his talk. Prof. Ding also presented the preparation and progress of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) to the workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p>Among the distinguished guests at the workshop are Renchang Hua, Vice President of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, Cher Wang, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean of SIST, Zhihe Rao, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean from School of Life Science and Technology, Yang Yang, Vice Dean of SIST, Hong Li, Vice Dean from School of Entrepreneurship and Management as well as Wenchi Chen, CEO of ViaTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_97\"></p>\n'),(84,'<p>2012年12月9-13日，由上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院发起并承办的“2012年国际前沿信息科学技术研讨会（FIST-2012），暨上海科技大学（筹）第二届国际科学家讲习班”在上海浦东张江博雅酒店隆重举行。<br>\n　　<br>\n　　此次研讨会邀请了来自世界一流学府和高科技跨国企业的60余位资深学者和世界级专家，会议围绕“探索信息科学领域的未来，展望信息科学领域科研及教育发展的远景”的主题， 通过61场精彩纷呈的学术报告，为200余位与会者提供了一场信息科学领域前沿科技的盛宴。<br>\n　　<br>\n　　此次研讨会主要分为11个讨论组，涵盖5大研究领域：“Future Data Technologies and Intelligent Systems”,“Information Theory and Foundations for future Communication and Energy Systems”,“Embedded Systems and Low Energy Electronics”,“Interdisciplinary Technologies”和“Next Generation Computing”。加州大学伯克利分校教授 David Tse 和IBM研究员 David Carmel 分别做了题为“The Science of Information: from Communication to DNA Sequencing”和“IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge”的大会主题报告，获得了与会专家和学者热情关注和积极讨论。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_85\"></p>\n\n<p>中科院上海分院院长江绵恒参加了开幕式并做了题为《Urbanization, Industrialization &amp; Informationization》的报告。报告以城镇化、工业化、信息化的发展为主线，指出了三化并举协同发展的中国特色发展道路，分析了现代社会信息化和全球化的发展趋势，点出了中国及中国科技和高等教育在这种全球信息化的大背景下寻求创新和突破的努力，最后强调了上海科技大学的使命和责任。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_86\"></p>\n\n<p>上海市教委副主任印杰代表上海科技大学筹建工作组介绍了上海科技大学建校的理念、学校规划和目前的筹建情况。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_87\"></p>\n\n<p>信息科学与技术学院丁峙教授主持了开幕式，并在会上代表信息科学与技术学院筹备小组，向与会嘉宾介绍了信息科学与技术学院的教学科研定位，展望了未来发展的方向和目前已经到位的师资和科研情况。</p>\n\n<p>　　上海科技大学执委会副主席华仁长，上海科技大学执委会成员、信息科学与技术学院筹建组负责人王雪红，上海科技大学执委会成员、生命科学与技术学院筹建组负责人饶子和，信息科学与技术学院筹建组成员杨旸、创业与管理学院筹建组成员李洪、威盛电子股份有限公司总经理陈文琦等均参加了此次研讨会。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_88\"></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(103,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(104,'<p>On December 28th, ShanghaiTech University laid its foundation in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), which marks substantial progress has been made in the preparatory work for establishing the university.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_149\"></p>\n\n<p>Ms. Yicui Yin，Deputy Secretary of the Shanghai CPC Committee, Prof. Erwei Shi, Vice President of CAS, Prof. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, along with Mr. Lin Xu, Secretary of Pudong New District CPC Committee, Mr. Xuebing Zhang and Mr. Xiaoming Shen, Vice Mayors of Shanghai Municipal Government, visited the laboratories of ShanghaiTech University and investigated the campus master plan.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_150\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_151\"></p>\n\n<p>Around 200 professors of ShanghaiTech University, leaders from departments of Shanghai Municipal Government and Pudong New Area Government, representatives from other universities in Shanghai, principals of CAS Shanghai Branch and institutes as well as delegates from partners involved in campus design and construction witnessed the launch of campus construction project altogether.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_152\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Bird\'s View</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_153\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Library</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_154\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Teaching Block</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_155\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Arts and Venue Street</p>\n\n<p>Located at the center of Zhangjiang high-tech industrial development zone, ShanghaiTech integrates with Shanghai Advanced Research Institute (SARI) in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park, which covers approximately one square kilometer. At the established Multidisciplinary Frontier Research Base in Pudong S&amp;T Park of CAS, room has been reserved for university’s laboratories, classrooms and offices. The laboratories have been initiated in advance.</p>\n'),(105,'<p>12月28日，上海科技大学（筹）校园建设在中国科学院上海浦东科技园正式启动，标志着上海科技大学筹建工作进入了实质性阶段。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_134\"></p>\n\n<p>上海市委副书记殷一璀，中科院副院长施尔畏，中科院上海分院院长江绵恒，上海市委常委、浦东新区区委书记徐麟，上海市副市长张学兵、沈晓明等视察了上海科技大学实验室，查看了上海科技大学规划建设情况。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_135\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_136\"></p>\n\n<p>上海科技大学约200位教授、上海市及浦东新区相关委办局领导、上海市其他高校代表、中科院上海分院及各研究院所负责同志、参与大学筹建和校园设计建设单位的代表共同见证了校园建设的启动。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_137\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">校园全景效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_138\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">图书馆效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_139\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">教学楼效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_140\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">生活与创业街效果图</p>\n\n<p>上海科技大学校区位于上海浦东张江国家高新示范区核心位置，与中科院上海高等研究院在中科院上海浦东科技园融为一体，总占地1265亩。在已建成的中科院上海浦东科技园交叉前沿基地，已经预留了学校校园建设期实验室、教学、办公的过渡性用房，实验室建设已先期启动。</p>\n'),(111,'<p>On May 11th, the ceremony marking the beginning of construction of ShanghaiTech University was held in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_115\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_116\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_117\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_118\"></p>\n'),(112,'<p>2013年5月11日，上海科技大学新校区工程开工仪式在中科院浦东科技园校园建设工地举行，标志着上海科技大学校园工程建设进入施工阶段。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_124\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_125\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_126\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_127\"></p>\n'),(164,'<p>On the morning of July 8th, ShanghaiTech 2013 summer camp for undergraduates formally kicked off in YueYang Road campus with 212 participants from 123 universities all over the country. Professor Mianheng Jiang, Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and President of Shanghai Branch, Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), handed the Camp flag over to the student representative on behalf of ShanghaiTech and initiated the camp. Professor Jie Yin, Vice Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Deputy Director of Shanghai Education Commission, Professor Jinkang Gong, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, as well as leaders of ShanghaiTech schools and institutes attended the opening ceremony.<br>\n<br>\nProfessor Mianheng Jiang delivered a speech named “Realizing China Dream through Innovation and Entrepreneurship”. He elaborated on the founding idea and mission of ShanghaiTech combined with national development strategy and social needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_165\"></p>\n\n<p>Professor Jie Yin outlined the preparation progress of ShanghaiTech University. ShanghaiTech University is characterized as a small-scale, high-level research university. It will tightly integrate education with innovative research and entrepreneurship to meet national and local development needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_166\"><br>\nProfessor Jinkang Gong explained in detail the training program of ShanghaiTech for graduate students, which ensures the implementation of the founding idea and the mission of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_167\"><br>\nIn the end of the ceremony, an overview of School of Physical Science and Technology (SPST), School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), School of Life Science and Technology (SLST), as well as School of Entrepreneurship and Management (SEM) was presented.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_168\"></p>\n\n<p>This was the 2nd Summer Camp held by ShanghaiTech University. Three schools respectively arranged a variety of activities for students according to their different subject characteristics. Participants of SPST will enter into different institutes of CAS Shanghai Branch, getting involved in group research, and students of SIST will compete in groups learning how to solve practical problems with classroom knowledge, while students of SLST will have the chance to join seminars where excellent reports will be presented by academicians and renowned scholars.</p>\n'),(174,'<p>7月8日上午，上海科技大学2013 “走进科研 体验创新”大学生夏令营在岳阳路园区正式开营，来自全国123所高校的212名同学参加了此次夏令营。上海科技大学执行委员会主席、中科院上海分院院长江 绵恒代表上海科技大学向营员代表授营旗并宣布夏令营正式开营。上海科技大学执行委员会副主席、上海市教育委员会副主任印杰，上海科技大学执行委员会成员龚 晋慷以及相关各学院、研究所领导出席了夏令营的开营仪式。</p>\n\n<p>开营仪式上，江绵恒做了题为“实现中国梦，创新+创业”的报告，报告从国家发展战略和经济社会需求出发，结合上海科技大学各学院的设置，向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的办学理念和使命。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_175\"></p>\n\n<p>印杰向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的概况，指出上海科技大学的办学目标是建设成小规模、高水平的国际化研究型大学，服务国家和上海的创新和转型。印杰还从学院与学科建设、教师队伍建设、校园建设等多个方面对上海科技大学筹建工作进展进行了介绍。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_176\"></p>\n\n<p>龚晋慷向同学们具体介绍了上海科技大学的研究生培养方案，从培养目标、培养模式、课程设置、学科方向与研究领域等多个方面进行了详细生动的解析，具体说明上海科技大学是如何将学校的办学理念、目标和使命落实在研究生的培养工作上。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_177\"></p>\n\n<p>最后，物质科学与技术学院、创业与管理学院、iHuman研究所和信息科学与技术学院的主要负责人分别介绍了各学院及研究所的概况与特色。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_178\"></p>\n\n<p>此次夏令营为上海科技大学举办的第二届大学生主题夏令营。本届夏令营的举办方式为 “让营员走进课题组、与导师零距离接触”，各学院也根据自己的学科特点和举办特色，为同学们安排了丰富多彩的活动。物质学院的营员将有充分的时间进入到中 科院上海分院各研究院所导师的课题组中，参与课题研究、了解学科动态；信息学院的营员将以分小组开展科技竞赛的形式，学习如何真正运用平时所学去解决实际 问题；而生命学院的营员在课题组实习之余，每天上午还将聆听到本领域内诸多院士和知名学者的精彩报告。</p>\n'),(184,'<p>8月9日—11日，上海科技大学首届高中生夏令营迎来了全国10个省市22所学校的154位高中生。上海科技大学执行委员会主席、中国科学院上海分院院长 江绵恒，上海科技大学执行委员会副主席、上海市教育委员会副主任印杰，上海科技大学执行委员会成员龚晋慷教授出席了开营式。</p>\n\n<p>开营式上，江绵恒做了题为“新一代年轻人立志、成才、报国、裕民的摇篮”的报告，报告从同学们即将面临的高三迎考引出话题，从国家发展战略和经济社会需求出发，结合上海科技大学各学院的设置，向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的办学理念和使命。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_185\"></p>\n\n<p>印杰向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的概况，指出上海科技大学的办学目标是建设成小规模、高水平的国际化研究型大学，服务国家和上海的创新和转型。印杰还从学院与学科建设、教师队伍建设、校园建设等多个方面对上海科技大学筹建工作进展进行了介绍。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_186\"></p>\n\n<p>龚晋慷向同学们具体介绍了上海科技大学的本科生培养方案，从培养目标、培养模式、书院制、国际交流等多个方面进行了详细生动的解析，具体说明上海科技大学是如何将学校的办学理念、目标和使命落实在本科生的培养工作上。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_187\"></p>\n\n<p>本届高中生夏令营主题为“走进‘科大’、走近科学、创想未来”。在为期三天的活动中，同学们通过破冰扬帆、走进科大、走近科学、走进上海、走近学者、创想 未来六大板块，与学校教授、教学设施、科研设备零距离接触。夏令营安排的各学科前沿讲座让学生全面直观了解到各领域前沿问题及研究方向，开拓了学生视野， 从而激发学生对科学探索的兴趣并确立远大的人生目标。夏令营着重培养学生的团队协作及沟通能力，鼓励营员在夏令营中相互之间增进了解，互相交流学习，提前 感受大学学习环境与文化氛围。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_188\"></p>\n'),(194,'<p>9月3日，上海科技大学首届研究生正式入学，296名新生在中科院上海浦东科技园共同迎来了开学第一天。在开学典礼现场见证他们踏上人生新征程的师长有来 自学校共建双方上海市与中科院上海分院及各研究院所的领导，包括12位两院院士在内的上科大教授，以及上科大的筹建团队。与此同时，在会场外不远处的上科 大校园建筑工地上，基建工作正在紧张有序地进行。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_195\"></p>\n\n<p>新大学，新气象。这次上科大新生入学的许多安排都体现出上科大“以人为本”、“改革创新”的办学理念。比如，在开学典礼上设置了介绍入学新生的环节，各学 院负责人逐一念出每一位学生的姓名，屏幕上同步显示出每位新生的照片、姓名和一句个性化的自我描述；在颁发学习用品的环节，上海科技大学筹建工作小组副组 长、上海市副市长翁铁慧为学生代表颁发了象征严谨求实的实验记录本，以及象征开启智慧之门的钥匙。当然，最集中体现上科大新起点、新格局、新理念的，还是 上海科技大学筹建工作小组组长、中科院上海分院院长江绵恒题为“立志、成才、报国、裕民”的主旨讲话。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_196\"></p>\n\n<p>江绵恒的讲话以中国梦为切入点，指出为了实现中国梦，为了应对未来经济社会发展的严峻挑战，我国正全力推进实施创新驱动、转型发展的国家战略，而上海科技 大学的设立就是为了服务这个国家战略。在他看来，移动互联网、物联网、云技术、先进机器人、全自动汽车、下一代基因组学、能量存储技术、先进纳米材料、 3D打印、可再生能源、第四代核反应堆、立体农业等一系列尖端科学技术将对未来人类生活和全球经济发展产生革命性的影响，而上海科技大学的设立就是要实现 科技和教育的紧密结合，要把科技和教育转变为生产力。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_197\"></p>\n\n<p>江绵恒希望上科大的研究生们要以造出龙飞船和特斯拉电动车、提出Hyperloop超级高铁设想的高科技创业家Elon Musk为榜样，培养创业激情与能力，为社会的发展和变革贡献实际的力量；以甘坐几十年冷板凳、终于破解世界级数学难题的数学家张益唐为榜样，踏实治学， 矢志不渝，为攀登科学高峰不断奋斗。</p>\n\n<p>江绵恒勉励同学们以实现中国梦为己任，选择奋斗、拼搏、奉献的青春，成为具有开拓和引领能力的创新、创业、创投人才，成就“立志、成才、报国、裕民”的高尚人生。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_198\"></p>\n\n<p>此外，在教授代表发言环节，上科大物质学院教授、中科院上海微系统所所长、中科院院士王曦以“感恩”、“坚持”、“创新”为主题，回顾了自己的科研和创业生涯，鼓励新生们敢于创新、勇于突破，永不言败，大至为国家、为社会，小至为实现自身的人生目标而不懈努力。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_199\"></p>\n\n<p>上科大iHuman研究所所长、中组部“外专千人计划”入选者Raymond C. Stevens在发言中表达了自己对科学发现的热情，以及对上科大发展前景的信心，他鼓励新生们要做自己命运的主人，相信“一分耕耘、一分收获”，最大限 度地利用好上科大提供的优质学术资源，挑战极限，探索真知。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_200\"></p>\n\n<p>在研究生代表发言环节，物质学院新生姜明超表达了自己作为上科大第一批学生的庆幸与自豪，以及自己对上科大“改革创新”、“以人为本”办学理念和“小规 模、高水平、国际化”办学特色的理解和认同。他倡议同学们肩负起上科大首届研究生的历史责任和使命，坚定立志报国的决心，发扬吃苦耐劳的精神，潜心科研， 锐意创新，向国家、向社会交出一份令人满意的答卷。</p>\n\n<p>开学典礼最后，江绵恒宣布上海科技大学首届（2013级）研究生正式开学。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_201\"></p>\n'),(210,'<p>ShanghaiTech’s first batch of 296 graduate students started their first day of 2013 semester on September 3rd. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_211\"></p>\n\n<p>The ceremony was organized in a novel and human-oriented format to match this brand new university. In front of the slideshow of the self-introduction of each student, the dean of each school announced the names of their students one by one. Madam Tiehui Weng, Deputy Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and Vice Mayor of Shanghai, granted each of the 3 student representatives an experiment record notebook and a crystal key as symbols of fact-finding spirit and pursuit of knowledge. What impressed the participants most was the exalting speech from Prof.Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_212\"><br>\nCentering around Jinping Xi’s “Chinese Dream”, Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_213\"></p>\n\n<p>Jiang encouraged the students to learn from Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who made Space X and Tesla the electrical car, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop the super high-speed train), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Jiang also mentioned the Chinese mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the “bounded gaps” conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_214\"></p>\n\n<p>As professor representatives, Xi Wang(Academician, Director of Shanghai Institute of Microsystem and Information Technology) and Raymond Stevens (Director of iHuman Institute of ShanghaiTech) reflected on their academic experience, expressed their excitement to join ShanghaiTech and encouraged the students to seize the day.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_215\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_216\"></p>\n\n<p>Mingchao Jiang, a student from School of Physical Science and Technology, gave the speech on behalf of the new students and talked about his understanding on innovation and human-centeredness.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_217\"></p>\n\n<p>At the end of the ceremony,Mianheng Jiang officially announced the opening of the semester. After the ceremony students had an interaction session with professors.</p>\n'),(226,'<p><span><span style=\"\"><span>296 young graduate students began their exciting ShanghaiTech career on September 3</span><sup><span>rd</span></sup><span>, 2013. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>The ceremony adopted non-traditional format to match this brand new university. Accompanied by slideshows, each school introduced their students one by one. Vice Major Tiehui Weng, Deputy Chief of the ShanghaiTech Preparation Work-Group, presented a lab notebook and a crystal key as symbols of truth searching spirit and pursuit of knowledge. As a highlight of the event, participants were treated by an exalting speech from Prof. Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Centering around the theme of “Chinese Dream”, Dr. Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Dr. Jiang encouraged the students to learn from individuals like Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who started Space X and Tesla, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Dr. Jiang also mentioned the example of a previously obscure mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the “bounded gaps” conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_227\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\"></span></span></p>\n'),(230,'<p>Two officers of the National Natural Science Foundation fo China, Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on September 28th.</p>\n\n<p>They received warm welcome by SIST faculty professors. Prof. Zhi Ding, Prof. Shuguang Cui and Prof. Pingqiang Zhou met Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, introduced our university and school, and had a constructive talk with them.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_231\"></p>\n'),(234,'<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_235\"></p>\n\n<p>9月28日，国家自然科学基金张兆田和熊晓媛两位专家来访我院，学院丁峙教授、崔曙光教授和周平强教授热情接待了两位专家，介绍了上海科技大学和信息科学与技术学院的基本情况，并在会谈中取得了富有建设性的共识。</p>\n'),(238,'<p>10月10日，信息学院成功举办“Young Idea Award”创意大赛，此项赛事的举办得到了学校财务处和创意与管理学院的大力支持。学院设立“Young Idea Award”创意大赛的目的是为鼓励那些有志于科学研究或创业研究生们，该项活动对全校研究生开放。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_263\"></p>\n\n<p>此次比赛有20多名研究生，共8个团队同场竞技，最终，以“创意校园”为主题的方案赢得了比赛，该方案由包宇洋、邢自然、贾翔宇3位同学共同完成。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_247\"></p>\n'),(239,'<p><span><span><span>A Contest named <em>Young Idea Award </em>was successfully held on November 10</span><sup><span>th</span></sup><span>, which was sponsored by SIST and received kind support from the office of Financial Services and the School of Entrepreneurship and Management at ShanghaiTech.<em> Young Idea Award </em>was designed for encouraging graduate students who have different and innovative understanding on scientific research or entrepreneurship. All the students from ShanghaiTech University were welcomed to join in the contest. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_259\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\"></p>\n\n<p><span>Over 20 students in eight teams took part in the contest. The topic named Creative Campus, which was designed by Yuying Bao, Xiangyu Jia, Ziran Xing from SIST, finally won the first prize.</span></p>\n\n<p><span><img src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_243\" alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\"></span></p>\n'),(250,'<p>10月29日至30日，丁峙教授和崔曙光教授代表上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院，赴北京参加了由未来移动通信论坛主办、墨提斯项目和中国移动协办的未来信息通讯技术高峰论坛和移动通讯技术工作坊。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_251\"></p>\n'),(254,'<p><span><span>On behalf of the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, </span><span><span>Prof. Zhi Ding and Prof. Shuguang Cui took part in</span></span><span><span> the Future (5G) ICT Summit &amp; 5G Mobile and Communication Technologies Workshop, which was Hosted by FuTURE FORUM, co-organized by METIS Project and China Mobile and held in Beijing during Oct 29th</span><span> – Oct 30th</span><span>. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_255\"></p>\n'),(267,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(268,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(277,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(287,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(376,'<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_378\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_379\"></p>\n\n<p>11月8日，斯坦福大学电气工程系教授Stephen Boyd受邀访问我院，并作了以“凸优化：从实时嵌入到大规模分布”为主题的学术报告。报告精彩纷呈，吸引了超过100位来自上科大、东南大学和上海大学的研究生和老师们，并激发了大家热烈的讨论。Stephen Boyd教授的报告聚焦于两个矛盾性的理论：实时嵌入凸优化和分布式凸优化，并分别作了深入浅出的阐述。报告结束后，Stephen Boyd教授与听众们作了深入的交流，并就如何开展高水平的研究与如何成为一个真正的学者进行了热烈的讨论。</p>\n'),(377,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(384,'<p>Prof. Stephen Boyd, Samsung Professor of Engineering, and a Professor of Electrical Engineering at Stanford University, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on November 8<sup>th</sup> and presented an exciting seminar on Convex Optimization: From Real-Time Embedded to Large-Scale Distributed. Over 100 graduated students and faculty members from ShanghaiTech, Southeast University and Shanghai University, enjoyed the high-quality seminar, which stimulated many productive discussions.  </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_385\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Boyd’s talk focused on two extremes: real-time embedded convex optimization, and distributed convex optimization. For the first one, code generation can be used to generate extremely efficient and reliable solvers for small problems, which can execute in milliseconds or microseconds, and are ideal for embedding in real-time systems. At the other extreme, Prof. Boyed described methods for large-scale distributed optimization, which coordinate many solvers to solve large problems. Prof. Boyd’s talk is open, humorous, informative, and inspiring. The large crowd at the seminar includes faculty members from as for as Nanjing. In addition, the Audience was also treated with some aspiring insightson how to conduct high-quality research and how to become a real scholar.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" style=\"line-height: 1.6;\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_386\"></p>\n'),(390,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(479,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(492,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(523,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(525,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(529,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(538,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(548,'<p><img title=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" id=\"plugin_obj_549\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugin