02, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage:  </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/liuxp/</p>\n'),(1732,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港中文大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>liuxp@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/liuxp/</p>\n'),(1733,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Computer Graphics (Fluid Simulation and Rendering)\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Fluid Dynamics (Visual Computing and Analysis)\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Scientific Visualization\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Image Analysis and Synthesis\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n GPU-based Parallel Computing<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Xiaopei Liu is an assistant professor at the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University. He eceived Ph.D. degree on computer science and engineering from the Chinese University of Hong Kong, and later did postdoctoral research as a Research Fellow at Nanyang Technological University in Singapore.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n His research interests are multidisciplinary on the areas of computer graphics, fluid dynamics, scientific visualization, and parallel computing. He have been intensively working with researchers on fluid dynamics and physics for such research. In addition, He have been interested in image analysis/synthesis techniques with a focus on illumination and texture analysis. He is also doing system and research work on the design and implementation of small unmanned aerial vehicles (S-UAV).\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Yulong Guo, Xiaopei Liu, Xuemiao Xu, A Unified Detail-Preserving Liquid Simulation by Two-Phase Lattice Boltzmann Modeling, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), 2016, accepted for publication.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Maneesh Mishra, Xiaopei Liu, Martin Skote, Chi-Wing Fu, Kolmogorov spectrum consistent optimization for multi-scale flow decomposition, AIP Physics of Fluids (POF), Vol. 26, No. 5, p.055106, 2014.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Wai-Man Pang, Jing Qin, Chi-Wing Fu, Turbulence Simulation by Adaptive Multi-Relaxation Lattice Boltzmann Modeling, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 20, No. 2, pp. 289-302, February, 2014.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Lei Jiang, Tien-Tsin Wong, Chi-Wing Fu, Statistical Invariance for Texture Synthesis, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 18, No. 11, pp. 1836-1848, November, 2012.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liang Wan, Xiaopei Liu, Tien-Tsin Wong, Chi-Sing Leung, Evolving Mazes from Images, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 16, No. 2, pp. 287-297, March-April, 2010.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Liang Wan, Yingge Qu, Tien-Tsin Wong, Stephen Lin, Chi-Sing Leung, Pheng-Ann Heng, Intrinsic Colorization, ACM Transactions on Graphics (TOG), SIGGRAPH Asia issue, Vol. 27, No. 5, December, 11-13, 2008.<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul><p></p>\n'),(1734,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算机图形学（流体仿真及渲染）\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 流体动力学（可视化计算与分析）\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 科学可视化\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 图像分析与合成\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 基于GPU的并行计算<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      刘晓培博士于2010年在香港中文大学计算机科学与工程系获得博士学位，之后在新加坡南洋理工大学从事博士后研究员工作。他目前的研究兴趣涵盖计算机图形学，流体动力学，科学可视化以及基于GPU的并行计算等多学科交叉领域。他早期从事图像分析与合成的相关工作。目前他大量和流体力学及物理学领域的研究人员合作，一起从事应用及理论科学研究。他的论文发表在多学科的期刊上，如ACM Transactions on Graphics，IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics，AIP Physics of Fluids，以及APS Physical Review D。刘晓培博士于2015年6月作为助理教授（终身教授序列）加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul><li>Yulong Guo, Xiaopei Liu, Xuemiao Xu, A Unified Detail-Preserving Liquid Simulation by Two-Phase Lattice Boltzmann Modeling, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), 2016, accepted for publication.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Maneesh Mishra, Xiaopei Liu, Martin Skote, Chi-Wing Fu, Kolmogorov spectrum consistent optimization for multi-scale flow decomposition, AIP Physics of Fluids (POF), Vol. 26, No. 5, p.055106, 2014.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Wai-Man Pang, Jing Qin, Chi-Wing Fu, Turbulence Simulation by Adaptive Multi-Relaxation Lattice Boltzmann Modeling, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 20, No. 2, pp. 289-302, February, 2014.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Lei Jiang, Tien-Tsin Wong, Chi-Wing Fu, Statistical Invariance for Texture Synthesis, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 18, No. 11, pp. 1836-1848, November, 2012.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liang Wan, Xiaopei Liu, Tien-Tsin Wong, Chi-Sing Leung, Evolving Mazes from Images, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics (TVCG), Vol. 16, No. 2, pp. 287-297, March-April, 2010.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Xiaopei Liu, Liang Wan, Yingge Qu, Tien-Tsin Wong, Stephen Lin, Chi-Sing Leung, Pheng-Ann Heng, Intrinsic Colorization, ACM Transactions on Graphics (TOG), SIGGRAPH Asia issue, Vol. 27, No. 5, December, 11-13, 2008.</li></ul><p></p>\n'),(1735,'<p>​<strong>博士: </strong>香港中文大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong>liuxp@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>计算机图形学（流体仿真及渲染）</li>\n	<li>流体动力学（可视化计算与分析）</li>\n	<li>科学可视化</li>\n	<li>图像分析与合成</li>\n	<li>基于GPU的并行计算<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(1736,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>liuxp@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 302, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Computer Graphics (Fluid Simulation and Rendering)</li>\n	<li>Fluid Dynamics (Visual Computing and Analysis)</li>\n	<li>Scientific Visualization</li>\n	<li>Image Analysis and Synthesis</li>\n	<li>GPU-based Parallel Computing<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(1737,'<p>Prof. Xiaopei Liu/刘晓培 助理教授</p>\n'),(1738,'<p>Prof. Xiaopei Liu/刘晓培 助理教授</p>\n'),(1741,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The University of Oklahoma</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/lujie/</p>\n'),(1742,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>俄克拉荷马大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/lujie/</p>\n'),(1743,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Distributed algorithms for in-network optimization and control\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Big data optimization and computation\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Coordination and decision making in multi-agent systems\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Cooperative wireless networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Convex optimization theory and algorithms\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Networked dynamical systems\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Jie Lu received the B.S. degree in Information Engineering from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2007 and the Ph.D. degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from the University of Oklahoma, USA in 2011. After that, she served as a postdoctoral researcher with the Automatic Control Laboratory at KTH Royal Institute of Technology and the Communication Systems Group at Chalmers University of Technology in Sweden. She will join the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University as an assistant professor from April 2015.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS<