Y. R. Li , Q. T. Sun and Ziyu Shao, \"Linear Network Coding: Theory and Algorithms\", Proceedings of the IEEE, vol. 99, no. 3, pp. 372-387, March, 2011.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1754,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 分布式算法与系统设计\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络优化\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络编码\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 云计算与移动计算\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      邵子瑜博士在北京大学电子学系获得学士与硕士学位，在香港中文大学信息工程系获得博士学位。加入上海科技大学之前在香港中文大学网络编码研究所从事博士后研究工作。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Ziyu Shao, M. Chen, S. Avestimehr, and S.-Y. R. Li, “Cross-layer Optimization for Wireless Networks with Deterministic Channel Models,” IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, vol.57, no.9, pp.5840 - 5862, Sep. 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Ziyu Shao, H. Zhang, M. Chen, and K. Ramchandran, \"Reverse-Engineering BitTorrent: A Markov Approximation Perspective\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2012, Orlando, Florida, USA, March 25-30, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Ziyu Shao, X. Jin, W. Jiang, M. Chen, and M. Chiang, \"Intra-Data-Center Traffic Engineering with Ensemble Routing\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2013, Torino, Italy, Apr. 14-19, 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. S.-Y. R. Li , Q. T. Sun and Ziyu Shao, \"Linear Network Coding: Theory and Algorithms\", Proceedings of the IEEE, vol. 99, no. 3, pp. 372-387, March, 2011.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1755,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>香港中文大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54205081<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼210室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>分布式算法与系统设计</li>\n	<li>网络优化</li>\n	<li>网络编码</li>\n	<li>云计算与移动计算</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1756,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54205081<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 210, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>distributed algorithm and system design</li>\n	<li>network coding</li>\n	<li>network optimization</li>\n	<li>cloud computing</li>\n	<li>mobile computing</li>\n	<li>smart grid</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1757,'<p>Prof. Ziyu Shao/邵子瑜 助理教授</p>\n'),(1758,'<p>Prof. Ziyu Shao/邵子瑜 助理教授</p>\n'),(1761,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Jacobs University Bremen</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54206163</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>soerensch@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office:  </strong>Room 103, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(1762,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>不来梅雅各布大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54206163</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>soerensch@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼103室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong></p>\n'),(1763,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Mobile Robotics</li>\n	<li>Robot Performance Evaluation, especially Map Evaluation</li>\n	<li>Mapping and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM)</li>\n	<li>Robot Autonomy and Intelligence</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p style=\"\">Dr. Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger</span> received his Diploma (German equivalent of the Master) in Computer Science in 2005 from the University of Bremen in Germany. In 2012 he received his Ph.D. in Computer Science from the Jacobs University Bremen, Germany. Between 2012 and 2014 he was a postdoctoral researcher at the Robotics Group of Prof. Andreas Birk at the Jacobs University Bremen. In 2010 Dr. Schwertfeger was a guest researcher at the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) in Gaithersburg, Maryland, USA, where he did research on robot performance evaluation and map quality assessment.</p>\n\n<p style=\"\">His research interest is in robotics, especially in intelligent functions for mobile robots. Besides his work on map evaluation, Dr. Schwertfeger also worked and published on mapping, object detection and robot autonomy. He successfully participated in many robot competitions, both as team member and as judge and organizer. Dr. Schwertfeger was the chair of the 2014 German Open RoboCup Rescue competition. In 2012 he won the best paper award at the International Workshop on Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics (SSRR). He is the reviewer for many top journals and conferences in the area of robotics.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\">[1] </span>Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger, Andreas Birk, \"Evaluation of Map Quality by Matching and Scoring High-Level, Topological Map Structures\", IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA), IEEE Press, 2013</span><br style=\"\">\n<span style=\"\">[2] </span>Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger, Andreas Birk, Heiko Bülow, \"Using iFMI Spectral Registration for Video Stabilization and Motion Detection by an Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV)\", International Workshop on Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics (SSRR), IEEE Press, 2011</span><br style=\"\">\n<span style=\"\">[3] Andreas Birk, </span>Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger, Kaustubh Pathak, \"A Networking Framework for Teleoperation in Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics\", Wireless Communications, IEEE Press, 2009</span><br style=\"\">\n<span style=\"\">[4] Kaustubh Pathak, Andreas Birk, Narunas Vaskevicius, Max Pfingsthorn, </span>Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger, Jann Poppinga, \"Online three‐dimensional SLAM by registration of large planar surface segments and closed‐form pose‐graph relaxation\", Journal of Field Robotics, Wiley, 2010</span><br style=\"\">\n<span style=\"\">[5] </span>Sören<span style=\"\"> Schwertfeger, Adam Jacoff, Chris Scrapper, Johannes Pellenz, Alexander Kleiner. \"Evaluation of maps using fixed shapes: The fiducial map metric\", Proceedings of the 10th Performance Metrics for Intelligent Systems Workshop, ACM, 2010</span></p>\n'),(1764,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Mobile Robotics\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Robot Performance Evaluation, especially Map Evaluation\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Mapping and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM)\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Robot Autonomy and Intelligence\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      Dr. S?ren Schwertfeger received his Diploma (German equivalent of the Master) in Computer Science in 2005 from the University of Bremen in Germany. In 2012 he received his Ph.D. in Computer Science from the Jacobs University Bremen, Germany. Between 2012 and 2014 he was a postdoctoral researcher at the Robotics Group of Prof. Andreas Birk at the Jacobs University Bremen. In 2010 Dr. Schwertfeger was a guest researcher at the National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST) in Gaithersburg, Maryland, USA, where he did research on robot performance evaluation and map quality assessment.\n <br>\n \n       His research interest is in robotics, especially in intelligent functions for mobile robots. Besides his work on map evaluation, Dr. Schwertfeger also worked and published on mapping, object detection and robot autonomy. He successfully participated in many robot competitions, both as team member and as judge and organizer. Dr. Schwertfeger was the chair of the 2014 German Open RoboCup Rescue competition. In 2012 he won the best paper award at the International Workshop on Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics (SSRR). He is the reviewer for many top journals and conferences in the area of robotics.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p>[1] Sören Schwertfeger, Andreas Birk, \"Evaluation of Map Quality by Matching and Scoring High-Level, Topological Map Structures\", IEEE International Conference on Robotics and Automation (ICRA), IEEE Press, 2013<br>\n \n [2] Sören Schwertfeger, Andreas Birk, Heiko Bülow, \"Using iFMI Spectral Registration for Video Stabilization and Motion Detection by an Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV)\", International Workshop on Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics (SSRR), IEEE Press, 2011<br>\n \n [3] Andreas Birk, Sören Schwertfeger, Kaustubh Pathak, \"A Networking Framework for Teleoperation in Safety, Security, and Rescue Robotics\", Wireless Communications, IEEE Press, 2009<br>\n \n [4] Kaustubh Pathak, Andreas Birk, Narunas Vaskevicius, Max Pfingsthorn, Sören Schwertfeger, Jann Poppinga, \"Online three‐dimensional SLAM by registration of large planar surface segments and closed‐form pose‐graph relaxation\", Journal of Field Robotics, Wiley, 2010<br>\n \n [5] Sören Schwertfeger, Adam Jacoff, Chris Scrapper, Johannes Pellenz, Alexander Kleiner. \"Evaluation of maps using fixed shapes: The fiducial map metric\", Proceedings of the 10th Performance Metrics for Intelligent Systems Workshop, ACM, 2010</p>\n'),(1765,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>不来梅雅各布大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54206163<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>soerensch@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼103室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Mobile Robotics</li>\n	<li>Robot Performance Evaluation, especially Map Evaluation</li>\n	<li>Mapping and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM)</li>\n	<li>Robot Autonomy and Intelligence</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1766,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Jacobs University Bremen<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54206163<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>soerensch@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 103, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Mobile Robotics</li>\n	<li>Robot Performance Evaluation, especially Map Evaluation</li>\n	<li>Mapping and Simultaneous Localization and Mapping (SLAM)</li>\n	<li>Robot Autonomy and Intelligence</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1767,'<p>Prof. Sören Schwertfeger/师泽仁 助理教授</p>\n'),(1768,'<p>Prof. Sören Schwertfeger/师泽仁 助理教授</p>\n'),(1771,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 217, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanming</p>\n'),(1772,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港科技大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼217室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanming</p>\n'),(1773,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"white-space: normal;\">\n \n <li>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n <b>Computational Big Data Analytics:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b>\n \n </p>\n \n Sparse and Low-Rank Models, Large-Scale Convex and Nonconvex Optimization, Riemannian Optimization, Randomized Sketching\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <b style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5;\">Mobile Edge/Fog Computing and Networking:</b><br>\n \n Caching, Computation Offloading, Privacy, Index Coding<br>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n <b>Dense Communication Networking:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b>\n \n </p>\n \n Cloud-RAN, Fog-RAN, Internet of Things (IoT), Tactile Internet\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Shi received the B.S. degree in electronic engineering from Tsinghua\n \n University, Beijing, China, in 2011. He received the Ph.D. degree in electronic\n \n and computer engineering from The Hong Kong University of Science and\n \n Technology (HKUST), in 2015, under the supervision of Prof. Khaled B. Letaief. Since\n \n September 2015, he has been with the School of Information Science and Technology in ShanghaiTech University, as a tenure-track Assistant\n \n Professor. Dr. Shi received the 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award in Wireless\n \n Communications.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n His research focuses on massive data analytics, computation, and\n \n communication (MC2) aspects in network science, including computational big\n \n data analytics, information-centric networking, mobile edge/fog computing and\n \n networking, IoT and Tactile Internet, sparse and low-rank models, convex and\n \n nonconvex optimization. \n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 1. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Low-rank matrix completion for\n \n topological interference management by Riemannian pursuit,” <i>IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun.</i>, vol. 15,\n \n no. 7, pp. 1-15, Jul. 2016.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 2. Y. Shi, J. Cheng, J. Zhang, B. Bai, W. Chen and K. B. Letaief,\n \n “Smoothed <i>Lp</i>-minimization for green\n \n Cloud-RAN with user admission control,” <i>IEEE\n \n J. Select. Areas Commun.</i>, vol. 34, no. 4, pp. 1-15, Apr. 2016.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 3. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, B. O’Donoghue, and K. B. Letaief, “Large-scale\n \n convex optimization for dense wireless cooperative networks,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63,\n \n no. 18, pp. 4729-4743, Sept. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 4. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Robust group sparse beamforming\n \n for multicast green Cloud-RAN with imperfect CSI,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63, no. 17, pp. 4647-4659, Sept.\n \n 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 5. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, K. B. Letaief, B. Bai, and W. Chen, “Large-scale\n \n convex optimization for ultra-dense Cloud-RAN,” <i>IEEE Wireless Commun. Mag</i>., vol. 22, no. 3, pp. 84-91, Jun. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 6. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Optimal stochastic coordinated\n \n beamforming for wireless cooperative networks with CSI uncertainty,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63,,\n \n no. 4, pp. 960-973, Feb. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n 7.\n \n Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Group sparse beamforming for green\n \n Cloud-RAN,” <i>IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun</i>.,\n \n vol. 13, no. 5, pp. 2809-2823, May 2014. (<b>The\n \n 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award</b>)<p></p>\n'),(1774,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算大数据分析\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 移动云（雾）计算\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 物联网及触感网络<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      石远明博士于2011年7月获得清华大学电子工程学士学位； 2015年8月获得香港科技大学电子及计算机工程博士学位。他于2015年9月加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院任助理教授。他的研究成果荣获2016 IEEE Marconi Prize Paper Award (马可尼论文奖)。他目前的研究兴趣主要包括计算大数据分析，移动云（雾）计算，物联网及触感网络，大规模优化理论与算法，黎曼优化。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Low-rank matrix completion for topological interference management by Riemannian pursuit,” IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun., vol. 15, no. 7, pp. 1-15, Jul. 2016. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 2. Y. Shi, J. Cheng, J. Zhang, B. Bai, W. Chen and K. B. Letaief, “Smoothed Lp-minimization for green Cloud-RAN with user admission control,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 34, no. 4, pp. 1-15, Apr. 2016. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 3. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, B. O’Donoghue, and K. B. Letaief, “Large-scale convex optimization for dense wireless cooperative networks,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63, no. 18, pp. 4729-4743, Sept. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 4. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Robust group sparse beamforming for multicast green Cloud-RAN with imperfect CSI,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63, no. 17, pp. 4647-4659, Sept. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 5. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, K. B. Letaief, B. Bai, and W. Chen, “Large-scale convex optimization for ultra-dense Cloud-RAN,” IEEE Wireless Commun. Mag., vol. 22, no. 3, pp. 84-91, Jun. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 6. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Optimal stochastic coordinated beamforming for wireless cooperative networks with CSI uncertainty,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63,, no. 4, pp. 960-973, Feb. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 7. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Group sparse beamforming for green Cloud-RAN,” IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun., vol. 13, no. 5, pp. 2809-2823, May 2014. (<strong>The 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award</strong>)<br></p>\n'),(1775,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>香港科技大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼217室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>计算大数据分析</li>\n	<li>移动云（雾）计算</li>\n	<li>物联网及触感网络<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(1776,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 217, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"white-space: normal;\">\n	<li>\n	<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Computational Big Data Analytics:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b></p>\n	Sparse and Low-Rank Models, Large-Scale Convex and Nonconvex Optimization, Riemannian Optimization, Randomized Sketching</li>\n	<li><b style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5;\">Mobile Edge/Fog Computing and Networking:</b><br>\n	Caching, Computation Offloading, Privacy, Index Coding</li>\n	<li>\n	<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Dense Communication Networking:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b></p>\n	Cloud-RAN, Fog-RAN, Internet of Things (IoT), Tactile Internet</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1777,'<p>Prof. Yuanming Shi/石远明 助理教授</p>\n'),(1778,'<p>Prof. Yuanming Shi/石远明 助理教授</p>\n'),(1781,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Université Paris Diderot</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>songfu@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(1782,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>巴黎狄德罗大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>songfu@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong></p>\n'),(1783,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Model-Checking\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n System analysis and verification\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Computer security\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Fu Song is an Assistant Professor as School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech. He received M.S. from East China Normal University in 2009 and Ph.D from Univeristy Paris Diderot (Paris 7) in 2013. After this Ph,D studies, he has been working in East China Normal Univeristy as Assistant Professor from 2013 to 2015 and Research Assoicate Professor since 2016, he also has been an invited research at Nanyang Technological University in 2014. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n His reearch interests broadly span model-checking, verification and automated analysis of systems and computer security. His paper on malware detection via pushdown model-checking won EASST best paper award at the18th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2012). \n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Verifying Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems against Strategy Logics. In Proc. of the 25th International Joint Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (IJCAI 2016). New York, USA. 9-15 July, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Global Model Checking on Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems. In Proc. of the 30th AAAI Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (AAAI 2016). Arizona, USA. 12-17 February, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Fu Song, Weikai Miao, Geguang Pu and Min Zhang. On Reachability Analysis of Pushdown Systems with Transductions: Application to Boolean Programs with Call-by-Reference. In Proc. of the 26th International Conference on Concurrency Theory (CONCUR 2015). Madrid, Spain. 1-4 September, 2015. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Efficient CTL Model-Checking for Pushdown Systems. Int. Journal on Theoretical Computer Science (TCS), Volume 549, 11 September 2014, Pages 127-145. DOI:10.1016/j.tcs.2014.07.001. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. LTL Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 19th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2013). Rome, Italy. March 16-24, 2013. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-36742-7_29. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Pushdown Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 18th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2012).Tallinn, Estonia. March 24-April 1, 2012. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-28756-5_9. This paper won the EASST best paper award at ETAPS 2012.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1784,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 模型检查\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 系统分析与验证\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算机安全\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      宋富博士于2009年6月获得华东师范大学软件工程硕士学位，2013年4月获得巴黎狄德罗大学（巴黎七大）计算机科学博士学位，同年8月加入华东师范大学任讲师，2016年1月破格晋升为副研究员，期间受新加坡南洋理工大学（NTU）邀请参加访问研究三个月，并于2015年分别荣获上海市“浦江人才”和上海市“晨光学者”称号。2016年8月全职加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院，担任tenure-track助理教授。宋富研究领域包括模型检查、系统自动分析与验证及在系统安全方面的应用，其提出的基于下推自动机模型检查的恶意软件检查方法在第18届TACAS/ETAPS国际会议上获得了欧洲软件科学与技术协会（EASST）颁发的最佳论文奖。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Verifying Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems against Strategy Logics. In Proc. of the 25th International Joint Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (IJCAI 2016). New York, USA. 9-15 July, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Global Model Checking on Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems. In Proc. of the 30th AAAI Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (AAAI 2016). Arizona, USA. 12-17 February, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Fu Song, Weikai Miao, Geguang Pu and Min Zhang. On Reachability Analysis of Pushdown Systems with Transductions: Application to Boolean Programs with Call-by-Reference. In Proc. of the 26th International Conference on Concurrency Theory (CONCUR 2015). Madrid, Spain. 1-4 September, 2015.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Efficient CTL Model-Checking for Pushdown Systems. Int. Journal on Theoretical Computer Science (TCS), Volume 549, 11 September 2014, Pages 127-145. DOI:10.1016/j.tcs.2014.07.001. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. LTL Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 19th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2013). Rome, Italy. March 16-24, 2013. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-36742-7_29. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Pushdown Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 18th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2012).Tallinn, Estonia. March 24-April 1, 2012. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-28756-5_9. This paper won the EASST best paper award at ETAPS 2012.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1785,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>巴黎狄德罗大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong>songfu@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>模型检查</li>\n	<li>系统分析与验证</li>\n	<li>计算机安全</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(1786,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Université Paris Diderot<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>songfu@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Model-Checking</li>\n	<li>System analysis and verification</li>\n	<li>Computer security</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(1787,'<p>Prof. Fu Song/宋富 助理教授</p>\n'),(1788,'<p>Prof. Fu Song/宋富 助理教授</p>\n'),(1791,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Iowa State University</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel:  </strong>(021)54205928</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>tukw@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office:  </strong>Room 203, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage:  </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/tukw/</p>\n'),(1792,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>爱荷华州立大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话:  </strong>(021)54205928</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>tukw@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼203室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页:  </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/tukw/</p>\n'),(1793,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Grammar Induction\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Machine Learning\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Natural Language Processing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Computer Vision\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Knowledge Representation and Reasoning\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>Kewei Tu received a PhD degree in Computer Science from Iowa State University, \n \n USA in 2012. During 2012-2014, he worked as a postdoctoral researcher at the \n \n Vision, Cognition, Learning and Art Laboratory, Departments of Statistics and \n \n Computer Science of the University of California, Los Angeles, USA. He has been \n \n an Assistant Professor with the School of Information Science and Technology at \n \n ShanghaiTech University, Shanghai, China since Feb 2014. His main research \n \n interests include machine learning of probabilistic grammars with applications \n \n in natural language processing and computer vision, and studying grammars as a \n \n general model of patterns for different aspects of human cognition.</p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Kewei Tu, Meng Meng, Mun Wai Lee, Tae Eun Choe and Song-Chun Zhu, \"Joint Video \n \n and Text Parsing for Understanding Events and Answering Queires \". To appear in \n \n IEEE MultiMedia.\n \n </p><p>\n \n 2. Kewei Tu, Maria Pavlovskaia and Song-Chun Zhu, \"Unsupervised Structure \n \n Learning of Stochastic And-Or Grammars\". In Advances in Neural Information \n \n Processing Systems 26 (NIPS 2013), Lake Tahoe, Nevada, USA, December 5-10, \n \n 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"Unambiguity Regularization for Unsupervised \n \n Learning of Probabilistic Grammars\". In Proceedings of the 2012 Conference on \n \n Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing and Natural Language Learning \n \n (EMNLP-CoNLL 2012), Jeju, Korea, July 12-14, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"On the Utility of Curricula in Unsupervised \n \n Learning of Probabilistic Grammars\". In Proceedings of the Twenty-second \n \n International Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence (IJCAI 2011), \n \n Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain, July 16-22, 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 5. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"Unsupervised Learning of Probabilistic \n \n Context-Free Grammar Using Iterative Biclustering\". In Proceedings of 9th \n \n International Colloquium on Grammatical Inference (ICGI 2008), LNCS 5278, St \n \n Malo, Brittany, France, September 22-24, 2008.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1794,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 机器学习\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 自然语言处理\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算机视觉等\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      屠可伟博士在上海交通大学计算机科学与工程系获得学士和硕士学位，在美国爱荷华州立大学计算机科学系获得博士学位。博士毕业后在美国加州大学洛杉矶分校统计系和计算机系从事博士后研究工作。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Kewei Tu, Meng Meng, Mun Wai Lee, Tae Eun Choe and Song-Chun Zhu, \"Joint Video and Text Parsing for Understanding Events and Answering Queires \". To appear in IEEE MultiMedia.\n \n </p><p>\n \n 2. Kewei Tu, Maria Pavlovskaia and Song-Chun Zhu, \"Unsupervised Structure Learning of Stochastic And-Or Grammars\". In Advances in Neural Information Processing Systems 26 (NIPS 2013), Lake Tahoe, Nevada, USA, December 5-10, 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"Unambiguity Regularization for Unsupervised Learning of Probabilistic Grammars\". In Proceedings of the 2012 Conference on Empirical Methods in Natural Language Processing and Natural Language Learning (EMNLP-CoNLL 2012), Jeju, Korea, July 12-14, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"On the Utility of Curricula in Unsupervised Learning of Probabilistic Grammars\". In Proceedings of the Twenty-second International Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence (IJCAI 2011), Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain, July 16-22, 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 5. Kewei Tu and Vasant Honavar, \"Unsupervised Learning of Probabilistic Context-Free Grammar Using Iterative Biclustering\". In Proceedings of 9th International Colloquium on Grammatical Inference (ICGI 2008), LNCS 5278, St Malo, Brittany, France, September 22-24, 2008.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1795,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>爱荷华州立大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021)54205928<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>tukw@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼203室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>机器学习</li>\n	<li>自然语言处理</li>\n	<li>计算机视觉等</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\