sing, electromagnetic interaction with human and\n \n biological tissues, antenna design for wireless communications, etc.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer,\n \n Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Impact of microwave pulses on thermoacoustic\n \n imaging applications,”IEEE Antennas and\n \n Wireless Propagation Letters, vol. 11, pp. 1634-1637, Nov. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer,\n \n Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Microwave-induced thermo-acoustic imaging model\n \n for potential breast cancer detection,”IEEETransactions\n \n on Biomedical Engineering,\n \n vol. 59, no. 10, pp. 2782-2791, Oct. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Daniel R. Bauer, Xiong Wang, Jeff\n \n L. Vollin, Hao Xin, and Russell S. Witte, “Spectroscopic thermoacoustic imaging\n \n of water and fat composition,”Appl.\n \n Phys. Lett., vol. 101, no. 3, pp. 033705-033705-4, Jul. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer,\n \n Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “A hybrid microwave / acoustic communication\n \n scheme - thermoacoustic communication,” 2013 IEEE International Microwave Symposium,\n \n Seattle, WA, Jun. 2-7, 2013.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1834,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 乳腺癌的热声成像检测\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 乳腺癌的微波热治疗\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 压缩感知\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 电磁波对人体和生物组织的影响\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 无线通信天线设计\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      王雄2014年在美国亚利桑那大学获得电子工程博士学位，2009年在美国克莱姆森大学获得电子工程硕士学位。他将于2015年6月作为助理教授加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院。他在2013年获得国际电气电子工程师协会天线与传播分会的2012-2013年度博士研究奖。他的研究兴趣包括：乳腺癌的热声成像检测，乳腺癌的微波热治疗，压缩感知，电磁波对人体和生物组织的影响，无线通信天线设计等。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Impact of microwave pulses on thermoacoustic imaging applications,” IEEE Antennas and Wireless Propagation Letters, vol. 11, pp. 1634-1637, Nov. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Microwave-induced thermo-acoustic imaging model for potential breast cancer detection,” IEEE Transactions on Biomedical Engineering, vol. 59, no. 10, pp. 2782?2791, Oct. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Daniel R. Bauer, Xiong Wang, Jeff L. Vollin, Hao Xin, and Russell S. Witte, “Spectroscopic thermoacoustic imaging of water and fat composition,” Appl. Phys. Lett., vol. 101, no. 3, pp. 033705-033705-4, Jul. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “A hybrid microwave / acoustic communication scheme - thermoacoustic communication,” 2013 IEEE International Microwave Symposium, Seattle, WA, Jun. 2-7, 2013.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1835,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>亚利桑那大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>wangxiong@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>\n	<div>乳腺癌的热声成像检测</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<div>乳腺癌的微波热治疗</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<div>压缩感知</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<div>电磁波对人体和生物组织的影响</div>\n	</li>\n	<li>\n	<div>无线通信天线设计</div>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1836,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The University of Arizona<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>wangxiong@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Thermoacoustic imaging for breast cancer detection</li>\n	<li>Microwave hyperthermia for breast cancer treatment</li>\n	<li>Compressive sensing</li>\n	<li>Electromagnetic interaction with human and biological tissues</li>\n	<li>Antenna design for wireless communications</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1837,'<p>Prof. Xiong Wang/王雄 助理教授</p>\n'),(1838,'<p>Prof. Xiong Wang/王雄 助理教授</p>\n'),(1841,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The City University of Hong Kong</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 212, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanxj/</p>\n'),(1842,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港城市大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼212室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanxj/</p>\n'),(1843,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Wireless communications\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Network information theory\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Compressed sensing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Smart grid<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>Dr. Xiaojun Yuan received the B.S. degree in Electronic and Information Systems from Shanghai Jiaotong University, the M.S. degree in Circuit and Systems from Fudan University, and the Ph.D. degree in Electrical Engineering from the City University of Hong Kong in 2008. From 2009 to 2011, he was a research fellow at the Department of Electronic Engineering, the City University of Hong Kong. He was a visiting scholar at the Department of Electrical Engineering, the University of Hawaii at Manoa in spring and summer 2009, as well as in the same period of 2010. From 2011 to 2014, he was a research assistant professor at the Institute of Network Coding, The Chinese University of Hong Kong. His research contributions cover a broad range of wireless communications, signal processing, and information theory problems including multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communications, rateless coding design, non-linear equalization, physical-layer network coding, cooperative communications, millimeter wave communications, etc. He has published over 60 peer-reviewed research papers in the leading international journals and conferences, and has served on a number of technical programs for 