d IEEE Multimedia, etc.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Y. Zheng, D. Cohen-Or, M. Averkiou, and N. Mitra., Recurring Part Arrangements in Shape Collections, Eurographics 2014(Best Paper Nomination).\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Y. Zheng, N. Mitra, and D. Cohen-Or., Smart Variations: Functional Substructures for Part Compatibility, Eurographics 2013(Best Paper Nomination).\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Y. Zheng, X. Cheng, M.-M. Cheng, K. Zhou, S.-M. Hu, and N. Mitra., Interactive Images: Cuboid-proxies for Smart Image Manipulation, ACM Transactions on Graphics TOG 2012 (SIGGRAPH).</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Y. Zheng, C.-L. Tai, Eugene Zhang, and Pengfei Xu, Pairwise Harmonics for Shape Analysis, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics. 2012.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Y. Zheng, C.-L. Tai, and O. K.-C. Au., Dot Scissor: A Single-Click Interface for Mesh Segmentation, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics. 2011.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1864,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 三维重建\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 3D打印\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 虚拟现实&amp;增强现实\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 人机交互<br>\n \n <div>\n \n <br>\n \n </div>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      郑友怡于2005年在浙江大学竺可桢学院获得理学学士学位，后于2007年获得浙江大学应用数学硕士学位，之后于香港科技大学计算机科学系获得博士学位。2011年博士毕业后在阿卜杜拉国王科技大学从事博士后研究，期间接受英国伦敦大学学院（UCL）的邀请参加访问研究。2013年9月在耶鲁大学计算机科学系从事博士后研究工作。郑友怡博士于2015年4月全职加入上海科技大学任信息科学与技术学院，任tenure-track助理教授。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Y. Zheng, D. Cohen-Or, M. Averkiou, and N. Mitra., Recurring Part Arrangements in Shape Collections, Eurographics 2014(最佳论文提名).\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Y. Zheng, N. Mitra, and D. Cohen-Or., Smart Variations: Functional Substructures for Part Compatibility, Eurographics 2013(最佳论文提名).\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Y. Zheng, X. Cheng, M.-M. Cheng, K. Zhou, S.-M. Hu, and N. Mitra., Interactive Images: Cuboid-proxies for Smart Image Manipulation, ACM Transactions on Graphics TOG 2012 (SIGGRAPH).</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Y. Zheng, C.-L. Tai, Eugene Zhang, and Pengfei Xu, Pairwise Harmonics for Shape Analysis, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics. 2012.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Y. Zheng, C.-L. Tai, and O. K.-C. Au., Dot Scissor: A Single-Click Interface for Mesh Segmentation, IEEE Transactions on Visualization and Computer Graphics. 2011.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1865,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>香港科技大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021)54206028<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhengyy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼304室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>三维重建</li>\n	<li>3D打印</li>\n	<li>虚拟现实&amp;增强现实</li>\n	<li>人机交互\n	<div> </div>\n	</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1866,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021)54206028<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhengyy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 304, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>3D Reconstruction</li>\n	<li>3D Printing</li>\n	<li>Virtual Reality &amp; Augmented Reality</li>\n	<li>Human Computer Interaction<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(1867,'<p>Prof. Youyi Zheng/郑友怡 助理教授 （青年千人）</p>\n'),(1868,'<p>Prof. Youyi Zheng/郑友怡 助理教授 （青年千人）</p>\n'),(1871,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>University of Minnesota, Twin Cities</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong>(021) 54201800</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 211, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/zhoupq/</p>\n'),(1872,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>明尼苏达大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54201800</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼211室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/zhoupq/</p>\n'),(1873,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n CAD of VLSI Circuits\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 3D Integrated Circuits\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Multicore Processors\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n On-Chip Communication Networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Simulation and Optimization of the Smart Grid\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Pingqiang Zhou received the M.E. degree from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 2007, and a Ph.D.degree from the University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, MN, USA, in 2012.He has been an Assistant Professor with the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, Shanghai, China, Since July 2013. Prior to joining ShanghaiTech, he was with the IBM T. J. Watson Research Center, Yorktown Heights, NY, USA, as a research intern, in 2011, also with the University of Minnesota as a Post-Doctoral Researcher from 2012 to 2013. His current research interests include computer-aided design of VLSI circuits, multicore processors, 3-D integration circuits, and the smart grid.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Prof. Zhou is the recipient of an Outstanding Masters Thesis Award from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China and the James Zeese Fellowship for his Ph.D. Thesis work from the University of Minnesota. He won the Intel/Helic/CICC Student Scholarship Award for top student papers at the IEEE Custom Integrated Circuits Conference and a Best Paper Award Nomination at the Asia/South Pacific Design Automation Conference. He is the reviewer for many top journals and conferences in the areas of VLSI design automation and computer architecture.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Pingqiang Zhou, Ping-Hung Yuh, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimized 3D Network-on-Chip Design Using Simulated Allocation,” ACM Transactions on Design Automation of Electronic Systems, Vol.17, No.2, pp.1-19, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Pingqiang Zhou, Bongjin Kim, Wonho Choi, Chris H. Kim, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimization of On-Chip Switched-Capacitor DC-DC Converters for High-Performance Applications,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp. 263-270, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Pingqiang Zhou, Jieming Yin, Antonia Zhai, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “NoC Frequency Scaling with Flexible-Pipeline Routers,” Proceedings of the ACM/IEEE International Symposium on Low Power Electronics and Design, pp.403-408, 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. Pingqiang Zhou, Karthikk Sridharan, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Power Grid Optimization in 3D Circuits Using MIM and CMOS Decoupling Capacitors,” IEEE Design &amp; Test, Vol.26, No.5, pp.15-25, 2009.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 5. Pingqiang Zhou, Yuchun Ma, Zhouyuan Li, Robert P. Dick, Li Shang, Hai Zhou, Xianlong Hong, and Qiang Zhou, “3D-STAF: Scalable Temperature and Leakage Aware Floorplanning for Three-dimensional Integrated Circuits,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp.590–597, 2007.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1874,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 集成电路与系统的计算机辅助设计\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      周平强博士2007年获得（北京）清华大学计算机科学与技术的硕士学位，2012年获得美国明尼苏达大学电气工程的博士学位，毕业后留校从事博士后研究工作2013年6月。周博士2013年7月1日加入上海科技大学信息学院。他曾获得清华大学优秀硕士论文奖以及明尼苏达大学博士论文奖学金。他在多核处理器的集成电压转换器上的创新性研究获得2011年国际定制集成电路会议（IEEE Custom Integrated Circuit Conference）的优秀学生论文奖学金；在三维多核处理器的通信网络上的研究成果获得亚太地区设计自动化会议（Asia/South Pacific Design Automation Conference）的最佳论文提名。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Pingqiang Zhou, Ping-Hung Yuh, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimized 3D Network-on-Chip Design Using Simulated Allocation,” ACM Transactions on Design Automation of Electronic Systems, Vol.17, No.2, pp.1-19, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Pingqiang Zhou, Bongjin Kim, Wonho Choi, Chris H. Kim, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimization of On-Chip Switched-Capacitor DC-DC Converters for High-Performance Applications,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp. 263-270, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Pingqiang Zhou, Jieming Yin, Antonia Zhai, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “NoC Frequency Scaling with Flexible-Pipeline Routers,” Proceedings of the ACM/IEEE International Symposium on Low Power Electronics and Design, pp.403-408, 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. Pingqiang Zhou, Karthikk Sridharan, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Power Grid Optimization in 3D Circuits Using MIM and CMOS Decoupling Capacitors,” IEEE Design &amp; Test, Vol.26, No.5, pp.15-25, 2009.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 5. Pingqiang Zhou, Yuchun Ma, Zhouyuan Li, Robert P. Dick, Li Shang, Hai Zhou, Xianlong Hong, and Qiang Zhou, “3D-STAF: Scalable Temperature and Leakage Aware Floorplanning for Three-dimensional Integrated Circuits,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp.590–597, 2007.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(1875,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>明尼苏达大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54201800<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼211室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>集成电路与系统的计算机辅助设计</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(1876,'<p>​<strong>Ph.D:  </strong>University of Minnesota, Twin Cities<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54201800<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 211, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>CAD of VLSI Circuits</li>\n	<li>3D Integrated Circuits</li>\n	<li>Multicore Processors</li>\n	<li>On-Chip Communication Networks</li>\n	<li>Simulation and Optimization of the Smart Grid</li>\n</ul>\n'),(1877,'<p>Prof. Pingqiang Zhou/周平强 助理教授</p>\n'),(1878,'<p>Prof. Pingqiang Zhou/周平强 助理教授</p>\n'),(1881,'<p><strong>Name: </strong>Cher Wang<br>\n<strong>Title: </strong>Dean<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong><br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(1882,'<p><strong>头衔: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>博士: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>zhiyong.bu@@mail.sim.ac.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong></p>\n'),(1883,'<p>Cher Wang has established a number of successful IT-related businesses, including founding VIA Technologies, Inc. and co-founding HTC Corporation. She is currently Chairwoman of both companies, and holds leadership roles in numerous other enterprises and organizations.</p>\n\n<p>Cher is active in the international business community, participating as an Industry Partner at the World Economic Forum and as a member of the APEC Business Advisory Council (ABAC). In 2010, Cher co-founded the ABAC Women’s Forum to identify capacity-building policy recommendations that enhance opportunities for women in business, and to hold outreach activities within APEC economies. Cher’s business achievements have been widely acclaimed in major international media.</p>\n\n<p>In addition to her business roles, Cher has always been devoted to giving back to the society with a keen focus on education. She fully embraces ShanghaiTech’s vision of emphasizing the integration of education, research and innovation, in order to further nurture outstanding talents engaged in scientific discovery, break-through inventions, and entrepreneurships.</p>\n\n<p>Cher graduated from the University of California, Berkeley, and is a devout Christian. She is married with two children.</p>\n'),(1884,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul