g></p>\n'),(6133,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>巴黎狄德罗大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email: </strong>songfu@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>模型检查</li>\n	<li>系统分析与验证</li>\n	<li>计算机安全</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(6134,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 模型检查\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 系统分析与验证\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算机安全\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      宋富博士于2009年6月获得华东师范大学软件工程硕士学位，2013年4月获得巴黎狄德罗大学（巴黎七大）计算机科学博士学位，同年8月加入华东师范大学任讲师，2016年1月破格晋升为副研究员，期间受新加坡南洋理工大学（NTU）邀请参加访问研究三个月，并于2015年分别荣获上海市“浦江人才”和上海市“晨光学者”称号。2016年8月全职加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院，担任tenure-track助理教授。宋富研究领域包括模型检查、系统自动分析与验证及在系统安全方面的应用，其提出的基于下推自动机模型检查的恶意软件检查方法在第18届TACAS/ETAPS国际会议上获得了欧洲软件科学与技术协会（EASST）颁发的最佳论文奖。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Verifying Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems against Strategy Logics. In Proc. of the 25th International Joint Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (IJCAI 2016). New York, USA. 9-15 July, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Taolue Chen, Fu Song* and Zhilin Wu. Global Model Checking on Pushdown Multi-Agent Systems. In Proc. of the 30th AAAI Conference on Artifficial Intelligence (AAAI 2016). Arizona, USA. 12-17 February, 2016. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Fu Song, Weikai Miao, Geguang Pu and Min Zhang. On Reachability Analysis of Pushdown Systems with Transductions: Application to Boolean Programs with Call-by-Reference. In Proc. of the 26th International Conference on Concurrency Theory (CONCUR 2015). Madrid, Spain. 1-4 September, 2015.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Efficient CTL Model-Checking for Pushdown Systems. Int. Journal on Theoretical Computer Science (TCS), Volume 549, 11 September 2014, Pages 127-145. DOI:10.1016/j.tcs.2014.07.001. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. LTL Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 19th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2013). Rome, Italy. March 16-24, 2013. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-36742-7_29. </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6. Fu Song and Tayssir Touili. Pushdown Model-Checking for Malware Detection. In Proc. of the 18th International Conference on Tools and Algorithms for the Construction and Analysis of Systems (TACAS 2012).Tallinn, Estonia. March 24-April 1, 2012. DOI:10.1007/978-3-642-28756-5_9. This paper won the EASST best paper award at ETAPS 2012.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6135,'<p>Prof. Fu Song/宋富 助理教授</p>\n'),(6137,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>Bielefeld University</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>ningcai@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(6138,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Bielefeld University<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>ningcai@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Network coding</li>\n	<li>Classical information theory</li>\n	<li>Quantum information theory<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6139,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Network coding\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Classical information theory\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Quantum information theory<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>Ning Cai received the B.S. degree in mathematics from the Normal College of Beijing, Beijing, China in 1982; the M.S. degree in mathematics from the Institute of System Science, Academia Sinica, Beijing, China, in 1984; and the Dr. degree in mathematics from the University of Bielefeld, Bielefeld, Germany, in 1988. During 1989-2005 he worked in the University of Bielefeld, Germany, the National University of Singapore, Singapore and the Chinese University of Hong Kong. Form 2006 to 2016 he was a distinguished professor Xidian University, China. He joined ShanghaiTech university in 2016. As a visiting professor, he visited the Technical University Of Munich, the Chinese University of Hong Kong, the University of Bielefeld , the University of South Australia, the Norwegian University of Science and Technology, and the University of Waterloo. Dr. Cai served as a IEEE IT Society Awards Committee member in 2008 and 2009, and a guest editor of joint Special Issue of IEEE Trans. on InformationTheory and IEEE/ACM Trans. on Networking, on “Networking and Information Theory”, 2006. He has served on the committees of a number of information theorysymposiums and workshops. Dr. Cai is a recipient of the 2005 IEEE Information Theory Society Paper Award for the paper “Linear network coding” and of the 2016 IEEE Eric. E. Sumner Award for “pioneering contributions to the field of network coding”, both with S-Y. R. Li and R. W. Yeung. He is a IEEE fellow. His research interests include network coding and classical and quantum information theory.</p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. R. Ahlswede and N. Cai, Arbitrarily varying multiple-access channels: Ericson’s symmetrizability is adequate, Gubner’s Conjecture is true, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory, V. 45, No. 2, 742-749, 1999 ; Part 2. Correlated sender’s side information, correlated messages, and ambiguous transmission,  IEEE Trans. on Information Theory, V. 45, No. 2, 749-756, 1999.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">2. R, Ahlswede, Ning Cai, S.-Y. R. Li and R. W. Yeung, Network information flow, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory”, V. 46, 1204-1216, 2000.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. S.-Y. R. Li and R. W. Yeung and N. Cai , Linear network coding, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory V.49, 371-381, 2003, (awarded paper).</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4.</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> N. Cai and R. W. Yeung, Secure Network Coding on a Wiretap Network, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory. V. 57, No. 1, pp 424-435, JANUARY 2011.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. N. Cai , Localized Error Correction in Projective Space, IEEE Trans. Inform Theory, v.59, pp. 3282-3294, 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6. H. Boche, N. Cai and J. N?tzel, The classical-quantum channel with random state parameters known to the sender, Journal of Physics A: Mathematical and Theoretical, (2016) 195302 (29pp) doi:10.1088/1751-8113/49/19/195302, 2016.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6140,'<p>Prof. Ning Cai/蔡宁 教授</p>\n'),(6142,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>比勒菲尔德大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>ningcai@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong></p>\n'),(6143,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>比勒菲尔德大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>ningcai@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>网络编码理论</li>\n	<li>经典信道</li>\n	<li>信源编码定理</li>\n	<li>量子信道编码定理<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6144,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络编码理论\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 经典信道\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 信源编码定理\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 量子信道编码定理<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      蔡宁于1982年在北京师范学院（现名首都师范大学）获得数学学士学位，1984年在中国科学院系统科学研究所获得数学硕士学位，1988年在德国比勒菲尔德大学（the University of Bielefeld）获得数学博士学位。从1989年到2005年，他在比勒菲尔德大学、新加坡国立大学和香港中文大学等高校从事研究工作。从2006年到2016年他在西安电子科技大学任特聘教授。他于2016年4月全职加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院任特聘教授。他2008 年和2009年曾担任IEEE信息论学会评奖委员会（IEEE IT Society Awards Committee）委员，并于2006年担任IEEE信息论学报（IEEE Trans. on Information Theory）和IEEE/ACM网络学报(IEEE/ACM Trans. on Networking)联合特刊“网络与信息论”（Special Issue“Networking and Information Theory”）的客座编辑（guest editor）. 他曾服务于多个信息论国际会议的各种组织委员会。他和李硕彦教授（S-Y. R. Li）和杨伟豪教授（R. W. Yeung）共同因论文“线性网络编码（Linear network coding）”获得2015年度IEEE信息论学会论文奖（the 2005 IEEE Information Theory Society Paper Award）；他们还因为“在网络编码领域中的先驱性贡献（pioneering contributions to the field of network coding）”一起获得2016年度的IEEE Eric. E. Sumner奖（the 2016 IEEE Eric. E. Sumner Award）。他是IEEE的fellow。 他当前的研究兴趣包括了网络编码及经典和量子信息论。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul><li>\n 1. R. Ahlswede and N. Cai, Arbitrarily varying multiple-access channels: Ericson’s symmetrizability is adequate, Gubner’s Conjecture is true, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory, V. 45, No. 2, 742-749, 1999 ; Part 2. Correlated sender’s side information, correlated messages, and ambiguous transmission,  IEEE Trans. on Information Theory, V. 45, No. 2, 749-756, 1999.\n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 2. R, Ahlswede, Ning Cai, S.-Y. R. Li and R. W. Yeung, Network information flow, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory”, V. 46, 1204-1216, 2000.\n </li>\n \n <li>\n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. S.-Y. R. Li and R. W. Yeung and N. Cai , Linear network coding, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory V.49, 371-381, 2003, (awarded paper).</span>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. N. Cai and R. W. Yeung, Secure Network Coding on a Wiretap Network, IEEE Trans. on Information Theory. V. 57, No. 1, pp 424-435, JANUARY 2011.</span>\n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. N. Cai , Localized Error Correction in Projective Space, IEEE Trans. Inform Theory, v.59, pp. 3282-3294, 2013.</span>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">6. H. Boche, N. Cai and J. N?tzel, The classical-quantum channel with random state parameters known to the sender, Journal of Physics A: Mathematical and Theoretical, (2016) 195302 (29pp) doi:10.1088/1751-8113/49/19/195302, 2016.</span>\n \n </li></ul><p></p>\n'),(6145,'<p>Prof. Ning Cai/蔡宁 教授 (IEEE Fellow)</p>\n'),(6147,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>Cornell University</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong>(021) 54201322</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>dingzhi@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 202, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong></p>\n'),(6148,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>Cornell University<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54201322<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>dingzhi@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 202, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Novel wireless digital communication system design and mplementations</li>\n	<li>MIMO wireless transceiver optimization and crosslayer integration</li>\n	<li>Cooperative wireless networking</li>\n	<li>Heterogeneous Wireless Networking</li>\n	<li>Distributed source localization</li>\n	<li>Joint detection and decoding receiver design and optimization</li>\n	<li>Fundamental signal processing</li>\n	<li>Structural health monitoring and stress-wave signal transmission</li>\n	<li>Adaptive and array signal processing<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6149,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Novel wireless digital communication system design and mplementations\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n MIMO wireless transceiver optimization and crosslayer integration\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Cooperative wireless networking\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Heterogeneous Wireless Networking\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Distributed source localization\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Joint detection and decoding receiver design and optimization\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Fundamental signal processing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Structural health monitoring and stress-wave signal transmission\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Adaptive and array signal processing<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Ding is a Professor of Electrical and Computer Engineering. He received the B.S. degree from Nanjing Institute of Technology in 1982, M.A.Sc. degree from the University of Toronto in 1987, and the Ph.D. degree from Cornell University in 1990, all in electrical engineering. He is currently Professor of Electrical and Computer Engineering, University of California, Davis, CA. His research contributions cover a broad range of signal processing and communication problems including wireless transceiver optimization,  blind channel estimation and equalization, multi-input-multi-output communications, multiuser detection, source separation, adaptive signal processing, parameter estimation, radar target discrimination, multimedia wireless communications,  and cross-layer wireless communications.  He has published over 200 refereed papers and book chapters.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Dr. Ding has served on a number of  technical programs for SPS workshops and conferences. He was associate editor for IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing from 1994-1997 and again from 2001-2004. He also served as  associate editor of IEEE Signal Processing Letters from 2002-2005. He was a member of technical committee on Statistical Signal and Array Processing,   member of technical committee on Signal Processing for Communications (1994-2003), and   a member of the IEEE SPS Technical Committee on Multimedia Signal Processing(2001-2006).  He was a member of the Editorial Board for the IEEE Signal Processing Magazine. Dr. Ding was on the Organization Committee of ICASSP 2005 in Philadelphia.  He was the Technical Program Chair of the 2006 IEEE Globecom. \n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Dr. Ding has held visiting positions in Australian National University, Hong Kong University of Science and Technology,   NASA Lewis Research Center, and USAF Wright Laboratory. Prof. Ding has active collaboration with researchers from several regions including Australia, China, Japan, Canada, Taiwan, Korea, Singapore, and Hong Kong. He is also a visiting professor of the Southeast University in Nanjing, China.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. T. Miyajima and Zhi Ding, \"Subcarrier Nulling Algorithms for Channel Shortening in Uplink OFDMA Systems, IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing, vol.60, no.5, pp.2374-2385, May 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. C. Xiao, Y. R. Zheng, and Z. Ding, \"Globally optimal linear precoders for finite alphabet signals over complex vector Gaussian channels, IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol.59, pp.3301-3314, July 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Li Zhang, Shu Lin, K. Abdel-Ghaffar, Zhi Ding, and Bo Zhou, \"Quasi-Cyclic LDPC Codes on Cyclic Subgroups of Finite Fields , IEEE Transactions on Communications, 59(9):2330-2336, Sept. 2011</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Z. Muhammad, and Z. Ding, \"Blind Multiuser Detection for Synchronous High Rate Space-Time Block Coded Transmission, IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, Issue: 99, July 2011, Page(s): 2171 - 2185.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. S. Bashar, Z. Ding, C. Xiao, \"On the Secrecy Rate of Multi-Antenna Wiretap Channel under Finite-Alphabet Input\", IEEE Communications Letters, Vol. 15, No. 5, 2011, Page(s): 527-529.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6150,'<p>Prof. Zhi Ding/丁峙 教授 (中央千人、IEEE Fellow)</p>\n'),(6152,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>康奈尔大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54201322</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>dingzhi@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼202室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong></p>\n'),(6153,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>康奈尔大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54201322<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>dingzhi@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼202室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">无线通信</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">信号处理</span></li>\n</ul>\n'),(6154,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">无线通信</span>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">信号处理<br>\n \n </span>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      丁峙教授1982年获得东南大学无线电工程系学士学位，1987年于加拿大多伦多大学电子工程系获硕士学位，1990年获得美国康奈尔大学电子工程学院博士学位。丁峙教授于2013年7月加入上海科技大学，在此之前任美国加州大学Davis分校电子与计算机工程系教授，系副主任。丁峙教授于2003年1月被推选为IEEE Fellow，后受聘为IEEE Fellows 评审委员会成员。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul><li>\n \n 1. T. Miyajima and Zhi Ding, \"Subcarrier Nulling Algorithms for Channel Shortening in Uplink OFDMA Systems, IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing, vol.60, no.5, pp.2374-2385, May 2012.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 2. C. Xiao, Y. R. Zheng, and Z. Ding, \"Globally optimal linear precoders for finite alphabet signals over complex vector Gaussian channels, IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol.59, pp.3301-3314, July 2011.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Li Zhang, Shu Lin, K. Abdel-Ghaffar, Zhi Ding, and Bo Zhou, \"Quasi-Cyclic LDPC Codes on Cyclic Subgroups of Finite Fields , IEEE Transactions on Communications, 59(9):2330-2336, Sept. 2011.</span>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Z. Muhammad, and Z. Ding, \"Blind Multiuser Detection for Synchronous High Rate Space-Time Block Coded Transmission, IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, Issue: 99, July 2011, Page(s): 2171 - 2185.</span>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. S. Bashar, Z. Ding, C. Xiao, \"On the Secrecy Rate of Multi-Antenna Wiretap Channel under Finite-Alphabet Input\", IEEE Communications Letters, Vol. 15, No. 5, 2011, Page(s): 527-529.</span></li>\n </ul><p></p>\n'),(6155,'<p>Prof. Zhi Ding/丁峙 教授 (中央千人、IEEE Fellow)</p>\n'),(6157,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong>(021) 54201338</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yangyang@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 204, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yangyang</p>\n'),(6158,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54201338<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>yangyang@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 204, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Medium Access Control Protocols</li>\n	<li>Heterogeneous Wireless Networks</li>\n	<li>Cooperative Radio Resource Management</li>\n	<li>Interference Coordination</li>\n	<li>Wireless Testbed and Practical Experiments<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6159,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Medium Access Control Protocols\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Heterogeneous Wireless Networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Cooperative Radio Resource Management\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Interference Coordination\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Wireless Testbed and Practical Experiments<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Yang Yang is currently a Professor with the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University, and the Director of Shanghai Research Center for Wireless Communications (WiCO). Prior to that, he has served Shanghai Institute of Microsystem and Information Technology (SIMIT), Chinese Academy of Sciences, as a Professor; the Department of Electronic and Electrical Engineering at University College London (UCL), United Kingdom, as a Senior Lecturer; the Department of Electronic and Computer Engineering at Brunel University, United Kingdom, as a Lecturer; and the Department of Information Engineering at The Chinese University of Hong Kong as an Assistant Professor.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Yang Yang received the BEng and MEng degrees in Radio Engineering from Southeast University, Nanjing, P. R. China, in 1996 and 1999, respectively; and the PhD degree in Information Engineering from The Chinese University of Hong Kong in 2002. His general research interests include wireless ad hoc and sensor networks, wireless mesh networks, next generation mobile cellular systems, intelligent transport systems, and wireless testbed development and practical experiments.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n [1] X. Chu, D. Lopez-Perez, Y. Yang, and F. Gunnarsson, “Heterogeneous Cellular Networks: Theory, Simulation and Deployment,” ISBN: 9781107023093, Cambridge University Press, 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n [2] G. Mao, Z. Lin, X. Ge, and Y. Yang, “Towards a Simple Relationship to Estimate the Capacity of Static and Mobile Wireless Networks,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, DOI: 10.1109/TWC.2013.-71113.121276, July 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">[3] J. Zhang, X. Ge, X. Li, G. Mao, and Y. Yang, “Analysis of the Uplink Maximum Achievable Rate with Location Dependent Inter-cell Signal Interference Factors Based on Linear Wyner Model,” IEEE Transactions on Vehicular Technology, DOI: 10.1109/TVT.2013.2265780, June 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">[4] R. Zhang, X. Cheng, Q. Yao, C-X. Wang, Y. Yang, and B. Jiao, “Interference Graph Based Resource Sharing Schemes for Vehicular Networks,” IEEE Transactions on Vehicular Technology, DOI: 10.1109/TVT.2013.2245156, Feb. 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">[5] W. Zhang, Y. Chen, Y. Yang, X. Wang, Y. Zhang, X. Hong, and G. Mao, “Multi-hop Access Probability and Connectivity Probability in Infrastructure-based Vehicular Networks,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), Vol. 30, No. 4, pp. 740-747, May 2012.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">[6] X. Dai, P. E. Omiyi, K. Bür, Kaan, and Y. Yang, “Interference-aware convergecast scheduling in wireless sensor/actuator networks for active airflow control applications,” Wireless Communication and Mobile Computing, DOI: 10.1002/wcm.2190, Feb. 2012.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6160,'<p>Prof. Yang Yang/杨旸 教授 （上海千人）</p>\n'),(6162,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港中文大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54201338</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yangyang@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼204室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yangyang</p>\n'),(6163,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>香港中文大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54201338<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>yangyang@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼204室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">新一代移动通信系统无线传感器网络</span></li>\n</ul>\n'),(6164,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">新一代移动通信系统无线传感器网络</span>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      1996年和1999年于东南大学无线电工程系获本科和硕士学位。2002年于香港中文大学信息工程系获博士学位。之后，留在香港中文大学信息工程系担任助理教授。2003年8月到英国布鲁奈尔大学（Brunel University）的电子与计算机工程系担任讲师。2005年3月到英国伦敦大学学院（UCL: University College London）电子与电气工程系担任讲师，后升职为高级讲师（终生教职）。在英国工作期间，与英国电信（British Telecom）、空中客车（Airbus）和劳斯莱斯（Rolls-Royce）等公司合作，自主研发了一系列高效率的媒质接入控制协议、路由协议和网络优化算法，在国际上率先将无线传感器网络技术应用于“飞机动态气流控制和磨擦阻力消减”（EP/F004532/1）和“飞机喷气式发动机中采集测试数据”（TS/G002614/1）等前沿课题。2008年，受中国科学院百人计划资助，杨旸回国加入中科院上海微系统与信息技术研究所任研究员，牵头承担了“新一代宽带无线移动通信网”国家科技重大专项的课题“IMT-Advanced关键技术试验平台开发”，带领研发团队构建了一个先进的、开放式、可扩展、可重构的室内外集成测试验证平台，包括多种实际无线通信场景和信道环境的模拟，系统性能的软硬件综合仿真、测试和评估，试验数据的采集和统计分析，以及无线宽带多媒体业务和新型无线服务的模拟和概念演示。2013年11月，全职加入上海科技大学。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul><li>1. W. X. Zhang, Y. Chen, Y. Yang, et al, “Multi-hop Connectivity Probability in Infrastructure-based Vehicular Networks,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications, Vol. 30, No. 4, May 2012.</li>\n \n <li>\n 2. X. Dai, P. E. Omiyi, K. Bür, and Y. Yang, “Interference-aware convergecast scheduling in wireless sensor/actuator networks for active airflow control applications,” Journal of Wireless Communications and Mobile Computing, to appear, Feb. 2012.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n 3. S. C. Ng, W. X. Zhang, Y. Zhang, Y. Yang, and G. Mao, “Analysis of Access and Connectivity Probabilities in Vehicular Relay Networks,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), Vol. 29, No. 1, pp. 140-150, Jan. 2011.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n 4. S. Sayed, Y. Yang, and J. Xu, “BTAC: A Busy Tone Based Cooperative MAC Protocol for Wireless Local Area Networks,” ACM Mobile Networks and Applications (MONE), Vol. 16, No. 1, pp. 4-16, Jan. 2010.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n 5. C. K. Chau, F. Qin, S. Sayed, M. H. Wahab, and Y. Yang, “Harnessing Battery Recovery Effect in Wireless Sensor Networks: Experiments and Analysis,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), Vol. 28, No. 7, pp. 1222-1232, Sept. 2010</li></ul><p></p>\n'),(6165,'<p>Prof. Yang Yang/杨旸 教授 (上海千人)</p>\n'),(6167,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>University of Minnesota</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong>(021) 54205213</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>luoxl@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 106, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/luoxl/</p>\n'),(6168,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>University of Minnesota<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54205213<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>luoxl@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 106, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>3GPP LTE/LTE-A, 5G</li>\n	<li>Heterogeneous Networks</li>\n	<li>Interference Coordination and Management in Next-Generation Wireless Networks</li>\n	<li>Massive MIMO</li>\n	<li>Indoor/Outdoor Positioning Theory and Technology (GPS, Beidou, Wireless Fingerprint etc.)<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6169,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 3GPP LTE/LTE-A, 5G\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Heterogeneous Networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Interference Coordination and Management in Next-Generation Wireless Networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Massive MIMO\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Indoor/Outdoor Positioning Theory and Technology (GPS, Beidou, Wireless Fingerprint etc.)<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>Xiliang Luo received his Bachelor of Science degree in Physics from the Peking University, Beijing, China, in 2001, and his Master of Science and Doctor of Philosophy degrees in Electrical Engineering from the University of Minnesota at Minneapolis in 2003 and 2006, respectively.<br>\n \n <br>\n \n Xiliang Luo was with SPiNCOM research group and led by Prof. Georgios B. Giannakis. Since 2006, after finishing his PhD studies, he has been working in Qualcomm Research at different posts: senior engineer (2006), staff engineer(2010), and then senior staff engineer(2013). His work in Qualcomm includes: system design, analyses, and standardization of 3GPP LTE starting from initial Rel-8 till current Rel-11. He was the designer of various enhancements to Qualcomm’s current LTE solutions and he has led the designs of Qualcomm’s next generation LTE modem for heterogeneous networks from initial concept to final completion.<br>\n \n <br>\n \n His general research interests lie in signal processing, communications, and information theory. In particular, he is interested in research combining information theory and signal processing theory that can shape and guide the designs of next eneration wireless networks beyond 4G LTE.</p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. A. Gorokhov, A. Farajidana, K. Bhattad, and X. Luo, “Multiple Antenna Techniques for LTE-Advanced,”     in LTE – The UMTS Long Term Evolution: from Theory to Practice, Editors: S. Sesia, I. Toufik, and M. Baker, John Wiley &amp; Sons, 2011.<br>\n \n 2. X. Luo, P. Gaal, W. Chen, X. Zhang, and J. Montojo, “Transmit Diversity Scheme over Single SC-FDM Symbol for LTE-Advanced,” in Proceedings of IEEE GLOBECOM’09, Honolulu, Hawaii, Nov. 30-Dec. 4, 2009.<br>\n \n 3. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Energy-Constrained Optimal Quantization for Wireless Sensor Networks,” EURASIP Journal on Advances in Signal Processing, Special Issue on Distributed Signal Processing Techniques for Wireless Sensor Networks, February 2008.<br>\n \n 4. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Raise Your Voice at a Proper Pace to Synchronize in Multiple Ad Hoc Piconets,” IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing, vol. 55, no. 1, pp. 267-278, January 2007<br>\n \n 5. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Low-Complexity Blind Synchronization and Demodulation for (Ultra-) Wideband Multi-User Ad Hoc Access,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 5, no. 7, pp. 1930-1941, July 2006.<br></p>\n'),(6170,'<p>Prof. Xiliang Luo/罗喜良 副教授 (青年千人)</p>\n'),(6172,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>明尼苏达大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54205213</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>luoxl@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼106室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/luoxl/</p>\n'),(6173,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>明尼苏达大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54205213<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>luoxl@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼106室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>下一代无线通信的关键理论和技术：</strong><br>\n	异质网络、干扰协调、大规模MIMO、定位技术 等</span></li>\n</ul>\n'),(6174,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>下一代无线通信的关键理论和技术：</strong><br>\n \n 异质网络、干扰协调、大规模MIMO、定位技术 等<br>\n \n </span>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      2001年北大物理系获得本科学位后赴美国明尼苏达大学双城分校留学，师从Giannakis老师，并于2006年获得电子工程博士学位。随后，加入位于加州圣地亚哥的无线通信领导者高通研发中心从事下一代无线通信系统的研究。在全职加入上科大前，在高通任高级主管工程师。在高通任职期间，参与了从LTE Rel-8到Rel-11的标准制定。同时，从最初的概念到最终的实现，领导研制了世界上第一款支持异质网络中参考信号干扰消除（RS-IC）的LTE 芯片（MDM9x35），极大地推动了刚在LTE-Advanced 标准中被定义并具有开创性的小区之间干扰协调技术(FeICIC)的商用化进程。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. A. Gorokhov, A. Farajidana, K. Bhattad, and X. Luo, “Multiple Antenna Techniques for LTE-Advanced,” in LTE – The UMTS Long Term Evolution: from Theory to Practice, Editors: S. Sesia, I. Toufik, and M. Baker, John Wiley &amp; Sons, 2011.<br>\n \n 2. X. Luo, P. Gaal, W. Chen, X. Zhang, and J. Montojo, “Transmit Diversity Scheme over Single SC-FDM Symbol for LTE-Advanced,” in Proceedings of IEEE GLOBECOM’09, Honolulu, Hawaii, Nov. 30-Dec. 4, 2009.<br>\n \n 3. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Energy-Constrained Optimal Quantization for Wireless Sensor Networks,” EURASIP Journal on Advances in Signal Processing, Special Issue on Distributed Signal Processing Techniques for Wireless Sensor Networks, February 2008.<br>\n \n 4. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Raise Your Voice at a Proper Pace to Synchronize in Multiple Ad Hoc Piconets,” IEEE Transactions on Signal Processing, vol. 55, no. 1, pp. 267-278, January 2007<br>\n \n 5. X. Luo and G. B. Giannakis, “Low-Complexity Blind Synchronization and Demodulation for (Ultra-) Wideband Multi-User Ad Hoc Access,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 5, no. 7, pp. 1930-1941, July 2006.<br>\n \n <br>\n \n 代表性专利：<br>\n \n 到目前为止，已经获得美国和国际授权专利超过30项。近期获得授权的代表性专利如下：<br>\n \n 1. “Interaction between Accumulative power Control and Minimum/Maximum Transmit Power in LTE Systems,” US 8,688,163, granted 2014/4<br>\n \n 2. “Cubic-Metric Based Frequency Selective Precoding for Uplink in MIMO Communication System,” US 8,687,728, granted 2014/4<br>\n \n 3. “Uplink Control Channel Resource Allocation for Transmit Diversity,” US 8,670,396, granted 2014/3<br>\n \n 4. “Over-The-Air Overload Indicator,” US 8,660,600, granted 2014/2<br>\n \n 5. “Multiple Signal Transformation in Wireless receivers,” US 8,655,282, granted 2014/2<br></p>\n'),(6175,'<p>Prof. Xiliang Luo/罗喜良 副教授 (青年千人)</p>\n'),(6177,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The City University of Hong Kong</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 212, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanxj/</p>\n'),(6178,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The City University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 212, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Wireless communications</li>\n	<li>Network information theory</li>\n	<li>Compressed sensing</li>\n	<li>Smart grid<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6179,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Wireless communications\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Network information theory\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Compressed sensing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Smart grid<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>Dr. Xiaojun Yuan received the B.S. degree in Electronic and Information Systems from Shanghai Jiaotong University, the M.S. degree in Circuit and Systems from Fudan University, and the Ph.D. degree in Electrical Engineering from the City University of Hong Kong in 2008. From 2009 to 2011, he was a research fellow at the Department of Electronic Engineering, the City University of Hong Kong. He was a visiting scholar at the Department of Electrical Engineering, the University of Hawaii at Manoa in spring and summer 2009, as well as in the same period of 2010. From 2011 to 2014, he was a research assistant professor at the Institute of Network Coding, The Chinese University of Hong Kong. His research contributions cover a broad range of wireless communications, signal processing, and information theory problems including multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) communications, rateless coding design, non-linear equalization, physical-layer network coding, cooperative communications, millimeter wave communications, etc. He has published over 60 peer-reviewed research papers in the leading international journals and conferences, and has served on a number of technical programs for international conferences.</p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Xiaojun Yuan, “MIMO multiway relaying with clustered full data exchange: Signal space alignment and degrees of freedom,” to appear in IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Xiaojun Yuan, Tao Yang, and Iain B. Collings, “Multiple-input multiple-output two-way relaying: A space-division approach,” IEEE Trans. Inform. Theory, vol. 59, no. 10, pp. 6421-6440, Oct. 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Jianwen Zhang, Xiaojun Yuan, and Li Ping, “Hermitian precoding for distributed MIMO systems with individual channel state information,” IEEE J. Sel. Areas Commun., vol. 31, no. 2, pp. 241-251, Feb. 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Xiaojun Yuan and Li Ping, “Quasi-systematic doped LT codes,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 27, no. 6, pp. 866-875, August 2009.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Xiaojun Yuan, Qinghua Guo, Xiaodong Wang, and Li Ping, “Evolution analysis of low-cost iterative equalization in coded linear systems with cyclic prefixes,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 26, no. 2, pp. 301-310, Feb. 2008.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6180,'<p>Prof. Xiaojun Yuan/袁晓军 助理教授 （青年千人）</p>\n'),(6182,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港城市大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼212室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanxj/</p>\n'),(6183,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>香港城市大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>yuanxj@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼212室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>无线通信</li>\n	<li>信号处理</li>\n	<li>信息论</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(6184,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 无线通信\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 信号处理\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 信息论<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"></span>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      袁晓军博士曾获得上海交通大学电子工程系的学士学位、复旦大学通信工程系的硕士学位，并于2008年获得香港城市大学电子工程系的博士学位。之后，留在香港城市大学担任电子工程系的研究员，并于2009年与2010年的春夏两季以访问学者的身份访问夏威夷大学马诺分校。2011年7月，袁晓军博士加入香港中文大学，成为网络编码研究所的助理教授。袁晓军博士于2014年7月全职加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院任助理教授（终身教授序列）。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Xiaojun Yuan, “MIMO multiway relaying with clustered full data exchange: Signal space alignment and degrees of freedom,” to appear in IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"></span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">2. Xiaojun Yuan, Tao Yang, and Iain B. Collings, “Multiple-input multiple-output two-way relaying: A space-division approach,” IEEE Trans. Inform. Theory, vol. 59, no. 10, pp. 6421-6440, Oct. 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">3. Jianwen Zhang, Xiaojun Yuan, and Li Ping, “Hermitian precoding for distributed MIMO systems with individual channel state information,” IEEE J. Sel. Areas Commun., vol. 31, no. 2, pp. 241-251, Feb. 2013.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">4. Xiaojun Yuan and Li Ping, “Quasi-systematic doped LT codes,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 27, no. 6, pp. 866-875, August 2009.</span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">5. Xiaojun Yuan, Qinghua Guo, Xiaodong Wang, and Li Ping, “Evolution analysis of low-cost iterative equalization in coded linear systems with cyclic prefixes,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 26, no. 2, pp. 301-310, Feb. 2008.</span>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6185,'<p>Prof. Xiaojun Yuan/袁晓军 助理教授 (青年千人)</p>\n'),(6187,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>fulq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 217, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/fulq</p>\n'),(6188,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>fulq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 217, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Distributed protocol design</li>\n	<li>Green wireless network</li>\n	<li>Network resource optimization</li>\n	<li>Wireless network control<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6189,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Distributed protocol design\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Green wireless network\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Network resource optimization\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Wireless network control<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Liqun Fu received the Ph.D. degree in Information Engineering from the Chinese University of Hong Kong in 2010, and the M.S. degree and the B.S degree (honors) both in Electrical Engineering from Tsinghua University and Xiamen University in 2006, and 2003, respectively. She visited Princeton University as a Visiting Scholar in 2009. From Sept. 2010 to Aug. 2015, she was a post-doctoral research fellow with the Institute of Network Coding of The Chinese University of Hong Kong first and then with the ACCESS post-doctoral researcher at the ACCESS Linnaeus Centre of KTH Royal Institute of Technology. She has joined the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University since Aug. 2015.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Her main research interests are in the area of wireless communication and networking, with current focus on green wireless, distributed algorithm and protocol design, signal processing, and wireless network optimization and control. She has published over 20 peer-reviewed research papers in the leading journals and prestigious conferences in the related field.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Ying Jun (Angela) Zhang, and Jianwei Huang, “Energy Efficient Transmissions in MIMO Cognitive Radio Networks,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), vol. 31, no. 11, pp. 2420-2431, Nov. 2013.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Effective Carrier Sensing in CSMA Networks under Cumulative Interference,” IEEE Transactions on Mobile Computing, vol. 12, no. 4, pp. 748-760, Apr. 2013.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Hongseok Kim, Jianwei Huang, Soung Chang Liew, and Mung Chiang, “Energy Conservation and Interference Mitigation: From Decoupling Property to Win-Win Strategy,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 10, no. 11, pp. 3943-3955, Nov. 2011.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Fast Algorithms for Joint Power Control and Scheduling in Wireless Networks,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 9, no. 3, pp. 1186-1197, Mar. 2010.\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Power Controlled Scheduling with Consecutive Transmission Constraints: Complexity Analysis and Algorithm Design,” in Proc. of the 28th Annual IEEE Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM), Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, Apr. 2009. (Acceptance rate: 19.6%)<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul><p></p>\n'),(6190,'<p>Prof. Liqun Fu/付立群 助理教授 (青年千人)</p>\n'),(6192,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港中文大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>fulq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼217室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/fulq</p>\n'),(6193,'<p><strong>博士:  </strong>香港中文大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>fulq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼217室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>分布式算法与网络设计</li>\n	<li>绿色通信</li>\n	<li>网络资源调度及优化</li>\n	<li>无线网络控制<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6194,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 分布式算法与网络设计\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 绿色通信\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络资源调度及优化\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 无线网络控制<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      付立群博士于2010年在香港中文大学信息工程学系获得博士学位,分别于2006年和2003年获得清华大学电子工程系硕士学位和厦门大学电子工程系学士学位（荣誉学士）。攻读博士学位期间，于2009年在普林斯顿大学访问半年。自2010年起至今，先后在香港中文大学网络编码研究所，瑞典皇家理工大学从事博士后研究工作。她目前的研究兴趣包括绿色通信，分布式算法与网络设计，信号处理，及无线网络控制等。近年以来，她在无线通信领域的国际重要期刊以及学术会议上发表学术论文二十余篇。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><ul><li>Liqun Fu, Ying Jun (Angela) Zhang, and Jianwei Huang, “Energy Efficient Transmissions in MIMO Cognitive Radio Networks,” IEEE Journal on Selected Areas in Communications (JSAC), vol. 31, no. 11, pp. 2420-2431, Nov. 2013.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Effective Carrier Sensing in CSMA Networks under Cumulative Interference,” IEEE Transactions on Mobile Computing, vol. 12, no. 4, pp. 748-760, Apr. 2013.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Hongseok Kim, Jianwei Huang, Soung Chang Liew, and Mung Chiang, “Energy Conservation and Interference Mitigation: From Decoupling Property to Win-Win Strategy,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 10, no. 11, pp. 3943-3955, Nov. 2011.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Fast Algorithms for Joint Power Control and Scheduling in Wireless Networks,” IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, vol. 9, no. 3, pp. 1186-1197, Mar. 2010.</li>\n \n <li>\n \n Liqun Fu, Soung Chang Liew, and Jianwei Huang, “Power Controlled Scheduling with Consecutive Transmission Constraints: Complexity Analysis and Algorithm Design,” in Proc. of the 28th Annual IEEE Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM), Rio de Janeiro, Brazil, Apr. 2009. (Acceptance rate: 19.6%)</li></ul><p></p>\n'),(6195,'<p>Prof. Liqun Fu/付立群 助理教授 (青年千人)</p>\n'),(6197,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The University of Oklahoma</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/lujie/</p>\n'),(6198,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The University of Oklahoma<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office: </strong><br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Distributed algorithms for in-network optimization and control</li>\n	<li>Big data optimization and computation</li>\n	<li>Coordination and decision making in multi-agent systems</li>\n	<li>Cooperative wireless networks</li>\n	<li>Convex optimization theory and algorithms</li>\n	<li>Networked dynamical systems</li>\n</ul>\n'),(6199,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n Distributed algorithms for in-network optimization and control\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Big data optimization and computation\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Coordination and decision making in multi-agent systems\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Cooperative wireless networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Convex optimization theory and algorithms\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Networked dynamical systems\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Jie Lu received the B.S. degree in Information Engineering from Shanghai Jiao Tong University in 2007 and the Ph.D. degree in Electrical and Computer Engineering from the University of Oklahoma, USA in 2011. After that, she served as a postdoctoral researcher with the Automatic Control Laboratory at KTH Royal Institute of Technology and the Communication Systems Group at Chalmers University of Technology in Sweden. She will join the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University as an assistant professor from April 2015.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. J. Lu and C. Y. Tang, \"Zero-Gradient-Sum Algorithms for Distributed Convex Optimization: The Continuous-Time Case,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 57, no. 9, pp. 2348-2354, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. J. Lu and C. Y. Tang, \"Controlled Hopwise Averaging and Its Convergence Rate,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 57, no. 4, pp. 1005-1012, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. J. Lu, C. Y. Tang, P. R. Regier, and T. D. Bow, \"Gossip Algorithms for Convex Consensus Optimization over Networks,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 56, no. 12, pp. 2917-2923, 2011.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6200,'<p>Prof. Jie Lu/陆疌 助理教授</p>\n'),(6202,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>俄克拉荷马大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/lujie/</p>\n'),(6203,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>俄克拉荷马大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>lujie@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室: </strong><br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">网络优化及控制分布式算法</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">多智能体系统的协调与决策</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">大数据优化与计算</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">合作无线网络中的探测，定位与调度问题</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">凸优化理论及算法</span></li>\n	<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">网络动力系统</span></li>\n</ul>\n'),(6204,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">网络优化及控制分布式算法</span> \n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">多智能体系统的协调与决策</span> \n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">大数据优化与计算</span> \n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">合作无线网络中的探测，定位与调度问题</span> \n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">凸优化理论及算法</span> \n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">网络动力系统</span><br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      陆疌于2007年本科毕业于上海交通大学信息工程系，并于2011年博士毕业于美国俄克拉荷马大学电子与计算机工程系。之后，她在瑞典皇家理工学院自动控制实验室与查尔姆斯理工大学通信系统组担任博士后研究员。陆疌的主要研究领域为多智能系统，信息物理融合系统(CPS)，合作无线网络，社会技术系统(STS)等网络系统应用中所产生的大规模优化与控制问题。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. J. Lu and C. Y. Tang, \"Zero-Gradient-Sum Algorithms for Distributed Convex Optimization: The Continuous-Time Case,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 57, no. 9, pp. 2348-2354, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. J. Lu and C. Y. Tang, \"Controlled Hopwise Averaging and Its Convergence Rate,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 57, no. 4, pp. 1005-1012, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. J. Lu, C. Y. Tang, P. R. Regier, and T. D. Bow, \"Gossip Algorithms for Convex Consensus Optimization over Networks,\" IEEE Transactions on Automatic Control, vol. 56, no. 12, pp. 2917-2923, 2011.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6205,'<p>Prof. Jie Lu/陆疌 助理教授</p>\n'),(6207,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 217, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanming</p>\n'),(6208,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology<br>\n<strong>Tel: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 217, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"white-space: normal;\">\n	<li>\n	<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Computational Big Data Analytics:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b></p>\n	Sparse and Low-Rank Models, Large-Scale Convex and Nonconvex Optimization, Riemannian Optimization, Randomized Sketching</li>\n	<li><b style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5;\">Mobile Edge/Fog Computing and Networking:</b><br>\n	Caching, Computation Offloading, Privacy, Index Coding</li>\n	<li>\n	<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\"><b>Dense Communication Networking:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b></p>\n	Cloud-RAN, Fog-RAN, Internet of Things (IoT), Tactile Internet</li>\n</ul>\n'),(6209,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul style=\"white-space: normal;\">\n \n <li>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n <b>Computational Big Data Analytics:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b>\n \n </p>\n \n Sparse and Low-Rank Models, Large-Scale Convex and Nonconvex Optimization, Riemannian Optimization, Randomized Sketching\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <b style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: 1.5;\">Mobile Edge/Fog Computing and Networking:</b><br>\n \n Caching, Computation Offloading, Privacy, Index Coding<br>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n <b>Dense Communication Networking:&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;</b>\n \n </p>\n \n Cloud-RAN, Fog-RAN, Internet of Things (IoT), Tactile Internet\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Shi received the B.S. degree in electronic engineering from Tsinghua\n \n University, Beijing, China, in 2011. He received the Ph.D. degree in electronic\n \n and computer engineering from The Hong Kong University of Science and\n \n Technology (HKUST), in 2015, under the supervision of Prof. Khaled B. Letaief. Since\n \n September 2015, he has been with the School of Information Science and Technology in ShanghaiTech University, as a tenure-track Assistant\n \n Professor. Dr. Shi received the 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award in Wireless\n \n Communications.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n His research focuses on massive data analytics, computation, and\n \n communication (MC2) aspects in network science, including computational big\n \n data analytics, information-centric networking, mobile edge/fog computing and\n \n networking, IoT and Tactile Internet, sparse and low-rank models, convex and\n \n nonconvex optimization. \n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 1. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Low-rank matrix completion for\n \n topological interference management by Riemannian pursuit,” <i>IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun.</i>, vol. 15,\n \n no. 7, pp. 1-15, Jul. 2016.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 2. Y. Shi, J. Cheng, J. Zhang, B. Bai, W. Chen and K. B. Letaief,\n \n “Smoothed <i>Lp</i>-minimization for green\n \n Cloud-RAN with user admission control,” <i>IEEE\n \n J. Select. Areas Commun.</i>, vol. 34, no. 4, pp. 1-15, Apr. 2016.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 3. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, B. O’Donoghue, and K. B. Letaief, “Large-scale\n \n convex optimization for dense wireless cooperative networks,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63,\n \n no. 18, pp. 4729-4743, Sept. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 4. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Robust group sparse beamforming\n \n for multicast green Cloud-RAN with imperfect CSI,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63, no. 17, pp. 4647-4659, Sept.\n \n 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 5. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, K. B. Letaief, B. Bai, and W. Chen, “Large-scale\n \n convex optimization for ultra-dense Cloud-RAN,” <i>IEEE Wireless Commun. Mag</i>., vol. 22, no. 3, pp. 84-91, Jun. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n <p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify;\">\n \n 6. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Optimal stochastic coordinated\n \n beamforming for wireless cooperative networks with CSI uncertainty,” <i>IEEE Trans. Signal Process</i>., vol. 63,,\n \n no. 4, pp. 960-973, Feb. 2015.<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"> </span>\n \n </p>\n \n 7.\n \n Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Group sparse beamforming for green\n \n Cloud-RAN,” <i>IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun</i>.,\n \n vol. 13, no. 5, pp. 2809-2823, May 2014. (<b>The\n \n 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award</b>)<p></p>\n'),(6210,'<p>Prof. Yuanming Shi/石远明 助理教授</p>\n'),(6212,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港科技大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼217室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/yuanming</p>\n'),(6213,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>香港科技大学<br>\n<strong>电话: </strong><br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shiym@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼217室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>计算大数据分析</li>\n	<li>移动云（雾）计算</li>\n	<li>物联网及触感网络<br>\n	 </li>\n</ul>\n'),(6214,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 计算大数据分析\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 移动云（雾）计算\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 物联网及触感网络<br>\n \n <br>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      石远明博士于2011年7月获得清华大学电子工程学士学位； 2015年8月获得香港科技大学电子及计算机工程博士学位。他于2015年9月加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院任助理教授。他的研究成果荣获2016 IEEE Marconi Prize Paper Award (马可尼论文奖)。他目前的研究兴趣主要包括计算大数据分析，移动云（雾）计算，物联网及触感网络，大规模优化理论与算法，黎曼优化。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Low-rank matrix completion for topological interference management by Riemannian pursuit,” IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun., vol. 15, no. 7, pp. 1-15, Jul. 2016. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 2. Y. Shi, J. Cheng, J. Zhang, B. Bai, W. Chen and K. B. Letaief, “Smoothed Lp-minimization for green Cloud-RAN with user admission control,” IEEE J. Select. Areas Commun., vol. 34, no. 4, pp. 1-15, Apr. 2016. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 3. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, B. O’Donoghue, and K. B. Letaief, “Large-scale convex optimization for dense wireless cooperative networks,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63, no. 18, pp. 4729-4743, Sept. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 4. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Robust group sparse beamforming for multicast green Cloud-RAN with imperfect CSI,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63, no. 17, pp. 4647-4659, Sept. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 5. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, K. B. Letaief, B. Bai, and W. Chen, “Large-scale convex optimization for ultra-dense Cloud-RAN,” IEEE Wireless Commun. Mag., vol. 22, no. 3, pp. 84-91, Jun. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 6. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Optimal stochastic coordinated beamforming for wireless cooperative networks with CSI uncertainty,” IEEE Trans. Signal Process., vol. 63,, no. 4, pp. 960-973, Feb. 2015. <br>\n \n <br>\n \n 7. Y. Shi, J. Zhang, and K. B. Letaief, “Group sparse beamforming for green Cloud-RAN,” IEEE Trans. Wireless Commun., vol. 13, no. 5, pp. 2809-2823, May 2014. (<strong>The 2016 Marconi Prize Paper Award</strong>)<br></p>\n'),(6215,'<p>Prof. Yuanming Shi/石远明 助理教授</p>\n'),(6217,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54205081</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:  </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office:  </strong>Room 210, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/shaozy/</p>\n'),(6218,'<p><strong>Ph.D:  </strong>The Chinese University of Hong Kong<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54205081<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 210, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>distributed algorithm and system design</li>\n	<li>network coding</li>\n	<li>network optimization</li>\n	<li>cloud computing</li>\n	<li>mobile computing</li>\n	<li>smart grid</li>\n</ul>\n'),(6219,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n distributed algorithm and system design\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n network coding\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n network optimization\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n cloud computing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n mobile computing\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n smart grid\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Dr. Ziyu Shao received the B.S. and M.E. degrees in electrical engineering \n \n from Peking University, Beijing, China, and the Ph.D. degree in information \n \n engineering from The Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shatin, N.T., Hong Kong. \n \n Currently, he is an Assistant Professor with the School of Information Science \n \n and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, Shanghai, China. Prior to joining \n \n ShanghaiTech, he was a Postdoctoral Fellow at Institute of Network Coding, The \n \n Chinese University of Hong Kong, Shatin, N.T., Hong Kong. His research interests \n \n include distributed algorithm and system design, network coding, network \n \n optimization, cloud computing, mobile computing, and smart grid. \n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Ziyu Shao, M. Chen, S. Avestimehr, and S.-Y. R. Li, “Cross-layer Optimization for Wireless Networks with Deterministic Channel Models,” IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, vol.57, no.9, pp.5840 - 5862, Sep. 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Ziyu Shao, H. Zhang, M. Chen, and K. Ramchandran, \"Reverse-Engineering BitTorrent: A Markov Approximation Perspective\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2012, Orlando, Florida, USA, March 25-30, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Ziyu Shao, X. Jin, W. Jiang, M. Chen, and M. Chiang, \"Intra-Data-Center Traffic Engineering with Ensemble Routing\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2013, Torino, Italy, Apr. 14-19, 2013.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. S.-Y. R. Li , Q. T. Sun and Ziyu Shao, \"Linear Network Coding: Theory and Algorithms\", Proceedings of the IEEE, vol. 99, no. 3, pp. 372-387, March, 2011.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6220,'<p>Prof. Ziyu Shao/邵子瑜 助理教授</p>\n'),(6222,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>香港中文大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54205081</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼210室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/shaozy/</p>\n'),(6223,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>香港中文大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54205081<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>shaozy@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼210室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>分布式算法与系统设计</li>\n	<li>网络优化</li>\n	<li>网络编码</li>\n	<li>云计算与移动计算</li>\n</ul>\n'),(6224,'<p><strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n 分布式算法与系统设计\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络优化\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 网络编码\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 云计算与移动计算\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      邵子瑜博士在北京大学电子学系获得学士与硕士学位，在香港中文大学信息工程系获得博士学位。加入上海科技大学之前在香港中文大学网络编码研究所从事博士后研究工作。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Ziyu Shao, M. Chen, S. Avestimehr, and S.-Y. R. Li, “Cross-layer Optimization for Wireless Networks with Deterministic Channel Models,” IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, vol.57, no.9, pp.5840 - 5862, Sep. 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Ziyu Shao, H. Zhang, M. Chen, and K. Ramchandran, \"Reverse-Engineering BitTorrent: A Markov Approximation Perspective\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2012, Orlando, Florida, USA, March 25-30, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Ziyu Shao, X. Jin, W. Jiang, M. Chen, and M. Chiang, \"Intra-Data-Center Traffic Engineering with Ensemble Routing\", in Proceedings of IEEE International Conference on Computer Communications (INFOCOM) 2013, Torino, Italy, Apr. 14-19, 2013.\n \n </p>