\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 电磁波对人体和生物组织的影响\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n <div>\n \n 无线通信天线设计\n \n </div>\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>个人简历</strong></p>\n\n<p>      王雄2014年在美国亚利桑那大学获得电子工程博士学位，2009年在美国克莱姆森大学获得电子工程硕士学位。他将于2015年6月作为助理教授加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院。他在2013年获得国际电气电子工程师协会天线与传播分会的2012-2013年度博士研究奖。他的研究兴趣包括：乳腺癌的热声成像检测，乳腺癌的微波热治疗，压缩感知，电磁波对人体和生物组织的影响，无线通信天线设计等。</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>代表性论文</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Impact of microwave pulses on thermoacoustic imaging applications,” IEEE Antennas and Wireless Propagation Letters, vol. 11, pp. 1634-1637, Nov. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “Microwave-induced thermo-acoustic imaging model for potential breast cancer detection,” IEEE Transactions on Biomedical Engineering, vol. 59, no. 10, pp. 2782?2791, Oct. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Daniel R. Bauer, Xiong Wang, Jeff L. Vollin, Hao Xin, and Russell S. Witte, “Spectroscopic thermoacoustic imaging of water and fat composition,” Appl. Phys. Lett., vol. 101, no. 3, pp. 033705-033705-4, Jul. 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Xiong Wang, Daniel R. Bauer, Russell S. Witte, and Hao Xin, “A hybrid microwave / acoustic communication scheme - thermoacoustic communication,” 2013 IEEE International Microwave Symposium, Seattle, WA, Jun. 2-7, 2013.\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6305,'<p>Prof. Xiong Wang/王雄 助理教授</p>\n'),(6307,'<p><strong>Ph.D: </strong>University of Minnesota, Twin Cities</p>\n\n<p><strong>Tel: </strong>(021) 54201800</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>Office: </strong>Room 211, Building 8</p>\n\n<p><strong>Homepage: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/zhoupq/</p>\n'),(6308,'<p>​<strong>Ph.D:  </strong>University of Minnesota, Twin Cities<br>\n<strong>Tel:  </strong>(021) 54201800<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>Office:  </strong>Room 211, Building 8<br>\n<strong>Research Interests:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>CAD of VLSI Circuits</li>\n	<li>3D Integrated Circuits</li>\n	<li>Multicore Processors</li>\n	<li>On-Chip Communication Networks</li>\n	<li>Simulation and Optimization of the Smart Grid</li>\n</ul>\n'),(6309,'<p><strong>RESEARCH INTERESTS</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n \n <li>\n \n CAD of VLSI Circuits\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n 3D Integrated Circuits\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Multicore Processors\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n On-Chip Communication Networks\n \n </li>\n \n <li>\n \n Simulation and Optimization of the Smart Grid\n \n </li>\n \n </ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>BIOGRAPHY</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n Pingqiang Zhou received the M.E. degree from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 2007, and a Ph.D.degree from the University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, MN, USA, in 2012.He has been an Assistant Professor with the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, Shanghai, China, Since July 2013. Prior to joining ShanghaiTech, he was with the IBM T. J. Watson Research Center, Yorktown Heights, NY, USA, as a research intern, in 2011, also with the University of Minnesota as a Post-Doctoral Researcher from 2012 to 2013. His current research interests include computer-aided design of VLSI circuits, multicore processors, 3-D integration circuits, and the smart grid.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n Prof. Zhou is the recipient of an Outstanding Masters Thesis Award from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China and the James Zeese Fellowship for his Ph.D. Thesis work from the University of Minnesota. He won the Intel/Helic/CICC Student Scholarship Award for top student papers at the IEEE Custom Integrated Circuits Conference and a Best Paper Award Nomination at the Asia/South Pacific Design Automation Conference. He is the reviewer for many top journals and conferences in the areas of VLSI design automation and computer architecture.\n \n </p><p></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>SELECTED PUBLICATIONS</strong></p>\n\n<p></p><p>\n \n 1. Pingqiang Zhou, Ping-Hung Yuh, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimized 3D Network-on-Chip Design Using Simulated Allocation,” ACM Transactions on Design Automation of Electronic Systems, Vol.17, No.2, pp.1-19, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 2. Pingqiang Zhou, Bongjin Kim, Wonho Choi, Chris H. Kim, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Optimization of On-Chip Switched-Capacitor DC-DC Converters for High-Performance Applications,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp. 263-270, 2012.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 3. Pingqiang Zhou, Jieming Yin, Antonia Zhai, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “NoC Frequency Scaling with Flexible-Pipeline Routers,” Proceedings of the ACM/IEEE International Symposium on Low Power Electronics and Design, pp.403-408, 2011.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 4. Pingqiang Zhou, Karthikk Sridharan, and Sachin S. Sapatnekar, “Power Grid Optimization in 3D Circuits Using MIM and CMOS Decoupling Capacitors,” IEEE Design &amp; Test, Vol.26, No.5, pp.15-25, 2009.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n 5. Pingqiang Zhou, Yuchun Ma, Zhouyuan Li, Robert P. Dick, Li Shang, Hai Zhou, Xianlong Hong, and Qiang Zhou, “3D-STAF: Scalable Temperature and Leakage Aware Floorplanning for Three-dimensional Integrated Circuits,” Proceedings of the IEEE/ACM International Conference on Computer-Aided Design, pp.590–597, 2007.\n \n </p>\n \n <p>\n \n <br>\n \n </p><p></p>\n'),(6310,'<p>Prof. Pingqiang Zhou/周平强 助理教授</p>\n'),(6312,'<p><strong>博士: </strong>明尼苏达大学</p>\n\n<p><strong>电话: </strong>(021) 54201800</p>\n\n<p><strong>Email: </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn</p>\n\n<p><strong>办公室: </strong>8号楼211室</p>\n\n<p><strong>个人主页: </strong>http://sist.shanghaitech.edu.cn/faculty/zhoupq/</p>\n'),(6313,'<p>​<strong>博士:  </strong>明尼苏达大学<br>\n<strong>电话:  </strong>(021) 54201800<br>\n<strong>Email:  </strong>zhoupq@@shanghaitech.edu.cn<br>\n<strong>办公室:  </strong>8号楼211室<br>\n<strong>研究领域:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>集成电路