送了大量人才。秉承教学、科研和公共参与相结合的办学思想，加州大学伯克利分校以其悠久的历史和优异的教学质量成为世界顶尖大学。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6619\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-2.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6620\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6621\"></p>\n'),(6622,'<p>October 29, 2012: Today, ShanghaiTech and the University of California, Berkeley signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to launch a collaboration in education, culture, and scientific research over the next five years. The signing ceremony was held at Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS). Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, and Dr. Robert J. Birgeneau, Chancellor of the University of California, Berkeley, signed the MoU. Dr. Renchang Hua, Chief Commander of Pudong Science and Technology Park, Dr. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, Ms. Cher Wang, Chairperson of VIA/HTC Group, Dr. Zihe Rao, Academician of CAS, Dr. Songlin Feng, President of the Shanghai Advanced Research Institute, CAS (SARI) and Dr. Jinkang Gong, Principal of International Affairs of ShanghaiTech University attended the ceremony along with delegates from UC Berkeley including Dr. Tsu-Jae King Liu, Electrical Engineering Division Chair and Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences Associate Chair, College of Engineering, Mr. Scott Biddy, Vice Chancellor for University Relations, Mr. David Jeu, Assistant Vice Chancellor for International Relations, as well as other staff with the delegation.<br>\n<br>\nShanghaiTech and UC Berkeley have agreed to be in partnership in education, culture and scientific research over the next five years. As a start to the education collaboration program, faculty in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences in the UC Berkeley College of Engineering, will share some of their core course instruction resources and instructional materials and references with a selection of courseware being developed for online format. For each course, ShanghaiTech University will send faculty members to UC Berkeley to learn their counterpart faculty member’s pedagogical and and research methodology.<br>\n<br>\nThe MoU signed between ShanghaiTech University and UC Berkeley represents a significant move for ShanghaiTech in promoting high-level international collaboration to boost disciplinary development and deepen its educational vision of sharing and openness in order to be a globally recognized research university.<br>\n<br>\nThe University of California, Berkeley serves as a world’s premier public research university. It is recognized as a major source of future talent. With the mission of teaching, research, and public service, UC Berkeley has earned its top ranking and global reputation through its time-honored history and outstanding academic achievements.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-IMG_0945_87RSPiY.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6623\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-2_F12jQL3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6624\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121113-1_uzBAveM.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6625\"></p>\n'),(6626,'<p>2012年12月9-13日，由上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院发起并承办的“2012年国际前沿信息科学技术研讨会（FIST-2012），暨上海科技大学（筹）第二届国际科学家讲习班”在上海浦东张江博雅酒店隆重举行。<br>\n　　<br>\n　　此次研讨会邀请了来自世界一流学府和高科技跨国企业的60余位资深学者和世界级专家，会议围绕“探索信息科学领域的未来，展望信息科学领域科研及教育发展的远景”的主题， 通过61场精彩纷呈的学术报告，为200余位与会者提供了一场信息科学领域前沿科技的盛宴。<br>\n　　<br>\n　　此次研讨会主要分为11个讨论组，涵盖5大研究领域：“Future Data Technologies and Intelligent Systems”,“Information Theory and Foundations for future Communication and Energy Systems”,“Embedded Systems and Low Energy Electronics”,“Interdisciplinary Technologies”和“Next Generation Computing”。加州大学伯克利分校教授 David Tse 和IBM研究员 David Carmel 分别做了题为“The Science of Information: from Communication to DNA Sequencing”和“IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge”的大会主题报告，获得了与会专家和学者热情关注和积极讨论。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6627\"></p>\n\n<p>中科院上海分院院长江绵恒参加了开幕式并做了题为《Urbanization, Industrialization &amp; Informationization》的报告。报告以城镇化、工业化、信息化的发展为主线，指出了三化并举协同发展的中国特色发展道路，分析了现代社会信息化和全球化的发展趋势，点出了中国及中国科技和高等教育在这种全球信息化的大背景下寻求创新和突破的努力，最后强调了上海科技大学的使命和责任。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6628\"></p>\n\n<p>上海市教委副主任印杰代表上海科技大学筹建工作组介绍了上海科技大学建校的理念、学校规划和目前的筹建情况。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6629\"></p>\n\n<p>信息科学与技术学院丁峙教授主持了开幕式，并在会上代表信息科学与技术学院筹备小组，向与会嘉宾介绍了信息科学与技术学院的教学科研定位，展望了未来发展的方向和目前已经到位的师资和科研情况。</p>\n\n<p>　　上海科技大学执委会副主席华仁长，上海科技大学执委会成员、信息科学与技术学院筹建组负责人王雪红，上海科技大学执委会成员、生命科学与技术学院筹建组负责人饶子和，信息科学与技术学院筹建组成员杨旸、创业与管理学院筹建组成员李洪、威盛电子股份有限公司总经理陈文琦等均参加了此次研讨会。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6630\"></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n'),(6631,'<p align=\"left\">ShanghaiTech University recently hosted a highly successful 2012 Frontiers of Information Science and Technology (FIST-2012) Workshop. FIST-2012 took place from December 9-13, 2012 at Parkyard Hotel, Zhangjiang Hi-tech Park, Pudong New Area, Shanghai. This high-level international workshop is initiated and organized by the School of Information Science and Technology. FIST-2012 workshop is one of a series of technical events during the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University. <br>\n<br>\nFIST-2012 invited over 60 major speakers from around the world, a large number of which are world-class senior researchers, professors and industrial experts. Focusing on the future development of scientific research and education in information science and technology, these distinguished speakers presented their recent exciting research findings, discussed important technological progresses, and articulated their visions on future research directions. More than 200 workshop participants took part in this unprecedented meeting of world class IT experts, covering a wide spectrum of frontier topics from big data, computer vision, to sub-millimeter wave imaging. FIST-2012 also invited Professor David Tse of UC Berkeley and IBM’s Dr. David Carmel to deliver two plenary lectures titled “The Science of Information: from Communications to DNA Sequencing” and “IBM Watson and the Jeopardy Challenge”, respectively. The plenary lectures stimulated a high level of attention and exciting discussions among workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p align=\"left\"><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-1_ud3iifC.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6632\"></p>\n\n<p>Dr. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, delivered the opening lecture titled “Urbanization, Industrialization, and Informationization” during the opening ceremony. Following the progress and modernization of society through, urbanization, industrialization, and the recent informationization, Dr. Jiang delineated the general development trend of society through information revolution and globalization. He further emphasized the necessity, importance, and urgency for China and China’s education system to break through traps and stagnation experienced earlier by nations in similar stage of development and modernization. Dr. Jiang introduced the inauguration of ShanghaiTech University as the government’s response and commitment to confront these difficult challenges. </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-2_N3urfAw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6633\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Jie Yin, Deputy Director of Shanghai Municipal Education Commission, presented the founding principles, the planning, and the current progress of ShanghaiTech University in his major speech on behalf of the ShanghaiTech University Steering Committee.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20121219-3_rRfZdVX.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6634\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Zhi Ding of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) served as the chair of the workshop and the opening ceremony. On behalf of Dean Cher Wang and the SIST team, he articulated the founding principles and future plan of SIST in his talk. Prof. Ding also presented the preparation and progress of the School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) to the workshop participants.</p>\n\n<p>Among the distinguished guests at the workshop are Renchang Hua, Vice President of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, Cher Wang, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean of SIST, Zhihe Rao, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Dean from School of Life Science and Technology, Yang Yang, Vice Dean of SIST, Hong Li, Vice Dean from School of Entrepreneurship and Management as well as Wenchi Chen, CEO of ViaTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121221-4_ySnnSEw.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6635\"></p>\n'),(6636,'<p>12月28日，上海科技大学（筹）校园建设在中国科学院上海浦东科技园正式启动，标志着上海科技大学筹建工作进入了实质性阶段。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6637\"></p>\n\n<p>上海市委副书记殷一璀，中科院副院长施尔畏，中科院上海分院院长江绵恒，上海市委常委、浦东新区区委书记徐麟，上海市副市长张学兵、沈晓明等视察了上海科技大学实验室，查看了上海科技大学规划建设情况。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6638\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6639\"></p>\n\n<p>上海科技大学约200位教授、上海市及浦东新区相关委办局领导、上海市其他高校代表、中科院上海分院及各研究院所负责同志、参与大学筹建和校园设计建设单位的代表共同见证了校园建设的启动。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6640\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">校园全景效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6641\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">图书馆效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6642\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">教学楼效果图</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6643\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">生活与创业街效果图</p>\n\n<p>上海科技大学校区位于上海浦东张江国家高新示范区核心位置，与中科院上海高等研究院在中科院上海浦东科技园融为一体，总占地1265亩。在已建成的中科院上海浦东科技园交叉前沿基地，已经预留了学校校园建设期实验室、教学、办公的过渡性用房，实验室建设已先期启动。</p>\n'),(6644,'<p>On December 28th, ShanghaiTech University laid its foundation in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), which marks substantial progress has been made in the preparatory work for establishing the university.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-1_TP3DDqk.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6645\"></p>\n\n<p>Ms. Yicui Yin，Deputy Secretary of the Shanghai CPC Committee, Prof. Erwei Shi, Vice President of CAS, Prof. Mianheng Jiang, President of CAS Shanghai Branch, along with Mr. Lin Xu, Secretary of Pudong New District CPC Committee, Mr. Xuebing Zhang and Mr. Xiaoming Shen, Vice Mayors of Shanghai Municipal Government, visited the laboratories of ShanghaiTech University and investigated the campus master plan.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-2_Jyy3iPK.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6646\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-3_Ej0Yt4b.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6647\"></p>\n\n<p>Around 200 professors of ShanghaiTech University, leaders from departments of Shanghai Municipal Government and Pudong New Area Government, representatives from other universities in Shanghai, principals of CAS Shanghai Branch and institutes as well as delegates from partners involved in campus design and construction witnessed the launch of campus construction project altogether.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-4_JnheOOm.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6648\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Bird\'s View</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-5_WgpppZb.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6649\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Library</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-6_e43iOqe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6650\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Teaching Block</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20121231-7_WiW6dLY.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6651\"></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Arts and Venue Street</p>\n\n<p>Located at the center of Zhangjiang high-tech industrial development zone, ShanghaiTech integrates with Shanghai Advanced Research Institute (SARI) in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science and Technology Park, which covers approximately one square kilometer. At the established Multidisciplinary Frontier Research Base in Pudong S&amp;T Park of CAS, room has been reserved for university’s laboratories, classrooms and offices. The laboratories have been initiated in advance.</p>\n'),(6652,'<p>2013年5月11日，上海科技大学新校区工程开工仪式在中科院浦东科技园校园建设工地举行，标志着上海科技大学校园工程建设进入施工阶段。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6653\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6654\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6655\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6656\"></p>\n'),(6657,'<p>On May 11th, the ceremony marking the beginning of construction of ShanghaiTech University was held in Pudong Science and Technology Park of Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS).</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-1_9KewrJE.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6658\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-2_CGoidJ1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6659\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-3_xDiEWpn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6660\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130515-4_K7R5wn1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6661\"></p>\n'),(6662,'<p>On the morning of July 8th, ShanghaiTech 2013 summer camp for undergraduates formally kicked off in YueYang Road campus with 212 participants from 123 universities all over the country. Professor Mianheng Jiang, Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and President of Shanghai Branch, Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), handed the Camp flag over to the student representative on behalf of ShanghaiTech and initiated the camp. Professor Jie Yin, Vice Chairman of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee and Deputy Director of Shanghai Education Commission, Professor Jinkang Gong, Member of ShanghaiTech Executive Committee, as well as leaders of ShanghaiTech schools and institutes attended the opening ceremony.<br>\n<br>\nProfessor Mianheng Jiang delivered a speech named “Realizing China Dream through Innovation and Entrepreneurship”. He elaborated on the founding idea and mission of ShanghaiTech combined with national development strategy and social needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_uW6jad6.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6663\"></p>\n\n<p>Professor Jie Yin outlined the preparation progress of ShanghaiTech University. ShanghaiTech University is characterized as a small-scale, high-level research university. It will tightly integrate education with innovative research and entrepreneurship to meet national and local development needs.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_UuzZRDW.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6664\"><br>\nProfessor Jinkang Gong explained in detail the training program of ShanghaiTech for graduate students, which ensures the implementation of the founding idea and the mission of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_psrEDRF.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6665\"><br>\nIn the end of the ceremony, an overview of School of Physical Science and Technology (SPST), School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), School of Life Science and Technology (SLST), as well as School of Entrepreneurship and Management (SEM) was presented.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4_eJbJPnn.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6666\"></p>\n\n<p>This was the 2nd Summer Camp held by ShanghaiTech University. Three schools respectively arranged a variety of activities for students according to their different subject characteristics. Participants of SPST will enter into different institutes of CAS Shanghai Branch, getting involved in group research, and students of SIST will compete in groups learning how to solve practical problems with classroom knowledge, while students of SLST will have the chance to join seminars where excellent reports will be presented by academicians and renowned scholars.</p>\n'),(6667,'<p>7月8日上午，上海科技大学2013 “走进科研 体验创新”大学生夏令营在岳阳路园区正式开营，来自全国123所高校的212名同学参加了此次夏令营。上海科技大学执行委员会主席、中科院上海分院院长江 绵恒代表上海科技大学向营员代表授营旗并宣布夏令营正式开营。上海科技大学执行委员会副主席、上海市教育委员会副主任印杰，上海科技大学执行委员会成员龚 晋慷以及相关各学院、研究所领导出席了夏令营的开营仪式。</p>\n\n<p>开营仪式上，江绵恒做了题为“实现中国梦，创新+创业”的报告，报告从国家发展战略和经济社会需求出发，结合上海科技大学各学院的设置，向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的办学理念和使命。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-1_Qf1Adfm.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6668\"></p>\n\n<p>印杰向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的概况，指出上海科技大学的办学目标是建设成小规模、高水平的国际化研究型大学，服务国家和上海的创新和转型。印杰还从学院与学科建设、教师队伍建设、校园建设等多个方面对上海科技大学筹建工作进展进行了介绍。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-2_pY2mH8R.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6669\"></p>\n\n<p>龚晋慷向同学们具体介绍了上海科技大学的研究生培养方案，从培养目标、培养模式、课程设置、学科方向与研究领域等多个方面进行了详细生动的解析，具体说明上海科技大学是如何将学校的办学理念、目标和使命落实在研究生的培养工作上。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-3_NnkqS10.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6670\"></p>\n\n<p>最后，物质科学与技术学院、创业与管理学院、iHuman研究所和信息科学与技术学院的主要负责人分别介绍了各学院及研究所的概况与特色。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130711-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6671\"></p>\n\n<p>此次夏令营为上海科技大学举办的第二届大学生主题夏令营。本届夏令营的举办方式为 “让营员走进课题组、与导师零距离接触”，各学院也根据自己的学科特点和举办特色，为同学们安排了丰富多彩的活动。物质学院的营员将有充分的时间进入到中 科院上海分院各研究院所导师的课题组中，参与课题研究、了解学科动态；信息学院的营员将以分小组开展科技竞赛的形式，学习如何真正运用平时所学去解决实际 问题；而生命学院的营员在课题组实习之余，每天上午还将聆听到本领域内诸多院士和知名学者的精彩报告。</p>\n'),(6672,'<p>8月9日—11日，上海科技大学首届高中生夏令营迎来了全国10个省市22所学校的154位高中生。上海科技大学执行委员会主席、中国科学院上海分院院长 江绵恒，上海科技大学执行委员会副主席、上海市教育委员会副主任印杰，上海科技大学执行委员会成员龚晋慷教授出席了开营式。</p>\n\n<p>开营式上，江绵恒做了题为“新一代年轻人立志、成才、报国、裕民的摇篮”的报告，报告从同学们即将面临的高三迎考引出话题，从国家发展战略和经济社会需求出发，结合上海科技大学各学院的设置，向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的办学理念和使命。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-1.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6673\"></p>\n\n<p>印杰向同学们介绍了上海科技大学的概况，指出上海科技大学的办学目标是建设成小规模、高水平的国际化研究型大学，服务国家和上海的创新和转型。印杰还从学院与学科建设、教师队伍建设、校园建设等多个方面对上海科技大学筹建工作进展进行了介绍。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-2.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6674\"></p>\n\n<p>龚晋慷向同学们具体介绍了上海科技大学的本科生培养方案，从培养目标、培养模式、书院制、国际交流等多个方面进行了详细生动的解析，具体说明上海科技大学是如何将学校的办学理念、目标和使命落实在本科生的培养工作上。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-3.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6675\"></p>\n\n<p>本届高中生夏令营主题为“走进‘科大’、走近科学、创想未来”。在为期三天的活动中，同学们通过破冰扬帆、走进科大、走近科学、走进上海、走近学者、创想 未来六大板块，与学校教授、教学设施、科研设备零距离接触。夏令营安排的各学科前沿讲座让学生全面直观了解到各领域前沿问题及研究方向，开拓了学生视野， 从而激发学生对科学探索的兴趣并确立远大的人生目标。夏令营着重培养学生的团队协作及沟通能力，鼓励营员在夏令营中相互之间增进了解，互相交流学习，提前 感受大学学习环境与文化氛围。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 20130813-4.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6676\"></p>\n'),(6677,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6678,'<p>9月3日，上海科技大学首届研究生正式入学，296名新生在中科院上海浦东科技园共同迎来了开学第一天。在开学典礼现场见证他们踏上人生新征程的师长有来 自学校共建双方上海市与中科院上海分院及各研究院所的领导，包括12位两院院士在内的上科大教授，以及上科大的筹建团队。与此同时，在会场外不远处的上科 大校园建筑工地上，基建工作正在紧张有序地进行。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6679\"></p>\n\n<p>新大学，新气象。这次上科大新生入学的许多安排都体现出上科大“以人为本”、“改革创新”的办学理念。比如，在开学典礼上设置了介绍入学新生的环节，各学 院负责人逐一念出每一位学生的姓名，屏幕上同步显示出每位新生的照片、姓名和一句个性化的自我描述；在颁发学习用品的环节，上海科技大学筹建工作小组副组 长、上海市副市长翁铁慧为学生代表颁发了象征严谨求实的实验记录本，以及象征开启智慧之门的钥匙。当然，最集中体现上科大新起点、新格局、新理念的，还是 上海科技大学筹建工作小组组长、中科院上海分院院长江绵恒题为“立志、成才、报国、裕民”的主旨讲话。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6680\"></p>\n\n<p>江绵恒的讲话以中国梦为切入点，指出为了实现中国梦，为了应对未来经济社会发展的严峻挑战，我国正全力推进实施创新驱动、转型发展的国家战略，而上海科技 大学的设立就是为了服务这个国家战略。在他看来，移动互联网、物联网、云技术、先进机器人、全自动汽车、下一代基因组学、能量存储技术、先进纳米材料、 3D打印、可再生能源、第四代核反应堆、立体农业等一系列尖端科学技术将对未来人类生活和全球经济发展产生革命性的影响，而上海科技大学的设立就是要实现 科技和教育的紧密结合，要把科技和教育转变为生产力。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6681\"></p>\n\n<p>江绵恒希望上科大的研究生们要以造出龙飞船和特斯拉电动车、提出Hyperloop超级高铁设想的高科技创业家Elon Musk为榜样，培养创业激情与能力，为社会的发展和变革贡献实际的力量；以甘坐几十年冷板凳、终于破解世界级数学难题的数学家张益唐为榜样，踏实治学， 矢志不渝，为攀登科学高峰不断奋斗。</p>\n\n<p>江绵恒勉励同学们以实现中国梦为己任，选择奋斗、拼搏、奉献的青春，成为具有开拓和引领能力的创新、创业、创投人才，成就“立志、成才、报国、裕民”的高尚人生。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6682\"></p>\n\n<p>此外，在教授代表发言环节，上科大物质学院教授、中科院上海微系统所所长、中科院院士王曦以“感恩”、“坚持”、“创新”为主题，回顾了自己的科研和创业生涯，鼓励新生们敢于创新、勇于突破，永不言败，大至为国家、为社会，小至为实现自身的人生目标而不懈努力。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6683\"></p>\n\n<p>上科大iHuman研究所所长、中组部“外专千人计划”入选者Raymond C. Stevens在发言中表达了自己对科学发现的热情，以及对上科大发展前景的信心，他鼓励新生们要做自己命运的主人，相信“一分耕耘、一分收获”，最大限 度地利用好上科大提供的优质学术资源，挑战极限，探索真知。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6684\"></p>\n\n<p>在研究生代表发言环节，物质学院新生姜明超表达了自己作为上科大第一批学生的庆幸与自豪，以及自己对上科大“改革创新”、“以人为本”办学理念和“小规 模、高水平、国际化”办学特色的理解和认同。他倡议同学们肩负起上科大首届研究生的历史责任和使命，坚定立志报国的决心，发扬吃苦耐劳的精神，潜心科研， 锐意创新，向国家、向社会交出一份令人满意的答卷。</p>\n\n<p>开学典礼最后，江绵恒宣布上海科技大学首届（2013级）研究生正式开学。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6685\"></p>\n'),(6686,'<p>ShanghaiTech’s first batch of 296 graduate students started their first day of 2013 semester on September 3rd. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-1_SsCQCix.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6687\"></p>\n\n<p>The ceremony was organized in a novel and human-oriented format to match this brand new university. In front of the slideshow of the self-introduction of each student, the dean of each school announced the names of their students one by one. Madam Tiehui Weng, Deputy Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and Vice Mayor of Shanghai, granted each of the 3 student representatives an experiment record notebook and a crystal key as symbols of fact-finding spirit and pursuit of knowledge. What impressed the participants most was the exalting speech from Prof.Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-2_yUa0O3U.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6688\"><br>\nCentering around Jinping Xi’s “Chinese Dream”, Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-3_M242EmH.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6689\"></p>\n\n<p>Jiang encouraged the students to learn from Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who made Space X and Tesla the electrical car, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop the super high-speed train), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Jiang also mentioned the Chinese mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the “bounded gaps” conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-4_wPNOKe3.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6690\"></p>\n\n<p>As professor representatives, Xi Wang(Academician, Director of Shanghai Institute of Microsystem and Information Technology) and Raymond Stevens (Director of iHuman Institute of ShanghaiTech) reflected on their academic experience, expressed their excitement to join ShanghaiTech and encouraged the students to seize the day.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5_P6ts1Zd.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6691\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-6_Tke5VH9.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6692\"></p>\n\n<p>Mingchao Jiang, a student from School of Physical Science and Technology, gave the speech on behalf of the new students and talked about his understanding on innovation and human-centeredness.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-7_dtF30kv.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6693\"></p>\n\n<p>At the end of the ceremony,Mianheng Jiang officially announced the opening of the semester. After the ceremony students had an interaction session with professors.</p>\n'),(6694,'<p><span><span style=\"\"><span>296 young graduate students began their exciting ShanghaiTech career on September 3</span><sup><span>rd</span></sup><span>, 2013. The inauguration ceremony was held in CAS Shanghai Pudong Science Park, with leaders and participants from Shanghai Municipality, CAS Shanghai Branch, CAS research institutes, together with 12 Academicians and the faculty and staff of ShanghaiTech.</span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>The ceremony adopted non-traditional format to match this brand new university. Accompanied by slideshows, each school introduced their students one by one. Vice Major Tiehui Weng, Deputy Chief of the ShanghaiTech Preparation Work-Group, presented a lab notebook and a crystal key as symbols of truth searching spirit and pursuit of knowledge. As a highlight of the event, participants were treated by an exalting speech from Prof. Mianheng Jiang, Head of the Preparation Work Group of ShanghaiTech and President of CAS Shanghai Branch.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Centering around the theme of “Chinese Dream”, Dr. Jiang said that China was adopting a strategy of innovation-driven development and transition to realize the dream and to address the challenges in future economic and social development, and the establishment of ShanghaiTech was to serve this national strategy. He listed eleven cutting-edge technologies that could impact our future human life and global economic development: mobile internet, internet of things, cloud technology, advanced robotics, next-generation genomics, energy storage, advanced nanomaterials, 3D printing, renewable energy, generation IV Reactor, and multi-storied agriculture. ShanghaiTech will integrate technology and education and transform them into productivity.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span>Dr. Jiang encouraged the students to learn from individuals like Elon Musk (the American entrepreneur who started Space X and Tesla, and proposed the idea of Hyperloop), and develop the passion and competence for entrepreneurship to contribute to the development of society. Dr. Jiang also mentioned the example of a previously obscure mathematician Yitang Zhang who recently stunned the world by proving the “bounded gaps” conjecture about the distribution of prime number after many years of anonymity and hard life, as an example of commitment and perseverance in science.</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"\"><span><img alt=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20130903-5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6695\"></span></span></p>\n'),(6696,'<p>Two officers of the National Natural Science Foundation fo China, Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on September 28th.</p>\n\n<p>They received warm welcome by SIST faculty professors. Prof. Zhi Ding, Prof. Shuguang Cui and Prof. Pingqiang Zhou met Mr. Zhaotian Zhang and Ms. Xiaoyun Xiong, introduced our university and school, and had a constructive talk with them.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532_boPUFVB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6697\"></p>\n'),(6698,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402171045278532.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6699\"></p>\n\n<p>9月28日，国家自然科学基金张兆田和熊晓媛两位专家来访我院，学院丁峙教授、崔曙光教授和周平强教授热情接待了两位专家，介绍了上海科技大学和信息科学与技术学院的基本情况，并在会谈中取得了富有建设性的共识。</p>\n'),(6700,'<p><span><span><span>A Contest named <em>Young Idea Award </em>was successfully held on November 10</span><sup><span>th</span></sup><span>, which was sponsored by SIST and received kind support from the office of Financial Services and the School of Entrepreneurship and Management at ShanghaiTech.<em> Young Idea Award </em>was designed for encouraging graduate students who have different and innovative understanding on scientific research or entrepreneurship. All the students from ShanghaiTech University were welcomed to join in the contest. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6702\"></p>\n\n<p><span>Over 20 students in eight teams took part in the contest. The topic named Creative Campus, which was designed by Yuying Bao, Xiangyu Jia, Ziran Xing from SIST, finally won the first prize.</span></p>\n\n<p><span><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6701\"></span></p>\n'),(6703,'<p>10月10日，信息学院成功举办“Young Idea Award”创意大赛，此项赛事的举办得到了学校财务处和创意与管理学院的大力支持。学院设立“Young Idea Award”创意大赛的目的是为鼓励那些有志于科学研究或创业研究生们，该项活动对全校研究生开放。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402181514515245.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6705\"></p>\n\n<p>此次比赛有20多名研究生，共8个团队同场竞技，最终，以“创意校园”为主题的方案赢得了比赛，该方案由包宇洋、邢自然、贾翔宇3位同学共同完成。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101444127339.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6704\"></p>\n'),(6706,'<p>10月29日至30日，丁峙教授和崔曙光教授代表上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院，赴北京参加了由未来移动通信论坛主办、墨提斯项目和中国移动协办的未来信息通讯技术高峰论坛和移动通讯技术工作坊。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6707\"></p>\n'),(6708,'<p><span><span>On behalf of the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University, </span><span><span>Prof. Zhi Ding and Prof. Shuguang Cui took part in</span></span><span><span> the Future (5G) ICT Summit &amp; 5G Mobile and Communication Technologies Workshop, which was Hosted by FuTURE FORUM, co-organized by METIS Project and China Mobile and held in Beijing during Oct 29th</span><span> – Oct 30th</span><span>. </span></span></span></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" title=\"Picture - e3041418jw1e93omkt4mfj20qo0i5mz5_fZwIZWL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6709\"></p>\n'),(6710,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6711\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6712\"></p>\n\n<p>11月8日，斯坦福大学电气工程系教授Stephen Boyd受邀访问我院，并作了以“凸优化：从实时嵌入到大规模分布”为主题的学术报告。报告精彩纷呈，吸引了超过100位来自上科大、东南大学和上海大学的研究生和老师们，并激发了大家热烈的讨论。Stephen Boyd教授的报告聚焦于两个矛盾性的理论：实时嵌入凸优化和分布式凸优化，并分别作了深入浅出的阐述。报告结束后，Stephen Boyd教授与听众们作了深入的交流，并就如何开展高水平的研究与如何成为一个真正的学者进行了热烈的讨论。</p>\n'),(6713,'<p>Prof. Stephen Boyd, Samsung Professor of Engineering, and a Professor of Electrical Engineering at Stanford University, visited the School of Information Science and Technology at ShanghaiTech University on November 8<sup>th</sup> and presented an exciting seminar on Convex Optimization: From Real-Time Embedded to Large-Scale Distributed. Over 100 graduated students and faculty members from ShanghaiTech, Southeast University and Shanghai University, enjoyed the high-quality seminar, which stimulated many productive discussions.  </p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101437248652.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6714\"></p>\n\n<p>Prof. Boyd’s talk focused on two extremes: real-time embedded convex optimization, and distributed convex optimization. For the first one, code generation can be used to generate extremely efficient and reliable solvers for small problems, which can execute in milliseconds or microseconds, and are ideal for embedding in real-time systems. At the other extreme, Prof. Boyed described methods for large-scale distributed optimization, which coordinate many solvers to solve large problems. Prof. Boyd’s talk is open, humorous, informative, and inspiring. The large crowd at the seminar includes faculty members from as for as Nanjing. In addition, the Audience was also treated with some aspiring insightson how to conduct high-quality research and how to become a real scholar.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201402101436424307.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6715\"></p>\n'),(6716,'<p>上海科技大学校务委员会于2013年12月28日召开第一次会议，出席会议的校务委员会成员有：</p>\n\n<p>徐匡迪：第十届全国政协副主席、上海市人民政府原市长、中国工程院原院长、上海科技大学第一届校务委员会主任</p>\n\n<p>周小川：第十二届全国政协副主席、中国人民银行行长</p>\n\n<p>翁铁慧：上海市人民政府副市长、上海科技大学筹建工作小组副组长</p>\n\n<p>丁仲礼：中国科学院副院长、中国科学院教育委员会主任</p>\n\n<p>傅成玉：中国石油化工集团公司董事长、党组书记</p>\n\n<p>江绵恒：中国科学院上海分院院长、上海科技大学筹建领导小组副组长、筹建工作小组组长、执行委员会主席</p>\n\n<p>朱志远：中国科学院上海分院常务副院长、上海科技大学筹建领导小组成员</p>\n\n<p>会议由徐匡迪主任主持。</p>\n\n<p>根据已由院市双方核准的《上海科技大学章程》的规定，校务委员会是上海科技大学的行政决策和议事机构，由上海市人民政府委派代表、中国科学院委派代表、学校代表和社会知名人士组成，其主要职责包括：制订和修改学校章程；审定学校发展战略与规划；提名校长人选；根据校长的提名任免学校有关管理人员；听取并审定学校年度工作报告和财务预算、决算；对学校重大事项做出决策；决定其他需要校务委员会审议的事项等。</p>\n\n<p>会议听取了《上海科技大学章程》的说明；听取了学校办学理念和目标，教学、科研工作及人才队伍建设进展情况，校园建设进展情况，以及2014年主要工作的汇报；审议通过了《上海科技大学校务委员会议事规则》；审议通过了相关人事任命；原则同意上海科技大学2013年度财务决算及2014年度财务预算。会议还对其他重大事项进行了讨论。</p>\n\n<p>会议指出，上海科技大学在党的十八届三中全会关于深化教育领域综合改革战略的指导下，积极探索教育、科研、创新创业的深度融合，在办学体制、治理结构、办学与人才培养模式、人事制度、拨款制度等方面大胆改革创新，在建设过程中得到了上海市人民政府和中国科学院的大力支持，各项工作取得了重大进展。会议相信，在教育部、上海市、中科院的大力支持和学校全体教职员工的不懈努力下，上海科技大学将在2014年进一步改革创新、开拓进取，按既定目标推动各项工作取得新的成绩。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201403061346428421.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201403061346428421.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6717\"></p>\n'),(6718,'<p>The first meeting of the University Board of Trustees was held on December 28th 2013. The attending members are:</p>\n\n<p><em><strong>Xu Kuangdi</strong></em>, Vice Chairman of 10th CPPCC National Committee; former Mayor of Shanghai, former President of the Chinese Academy of Engineering; Chairman of the University Council of the University <br>\n<em><strong>Zhou Xiaochuan</strong></em>, Vice Chairman of 12th CPPCC National Committee; Governor of the People\'s Bank of China.<br>\n<em><strong>Weng Tiehui</strong></em><strong>,</strong> Vice Mayor of Shanghai; Deputy Head of the Working Group of ShanghaiTech.<br>\n<em><strong>Ding Zhongli</strong></em>, Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences; Director of the Education Committee of CAS.<br>\n<em><strong>Fu Chengyu</strong></em><strong>,</strong> Chairman of China Petroleum &amp; Chemical Corporation.<br>\n<em><strong>Jiang Mianheng</strong></em><strong>,</strong> President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch; Chairman of the Executive Committee of Shanghaitech.<br>\n<em><strong>Zhu Zhiyuan</strong></em><strong>,</strong> Executive Vice President of Chinese Academy of Sciences Shanghai Branch.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting was chaired by Xu Kuangdi.</p>\n\n<p>According to the By Laws of ShanghaiTech University approved by both CAS and Shanghai Municipality, the University Board of Trustees is the decision-making body of ShanghaiTech. It is composed of representatives from Shanghai Municipality, CAS, the university as well as expert from the industry. Its responsibilities include compiling and revising the By Laws, drafting the development strategy and plan; nominating the university President, appointing the administrative heads based on the President\'s nomination, reviewing the annual report, budget and final account, deciding the key issues of the university and etc,.</p>\n\n<p>The meeting reviewed the vision and goals of the university, the current status of teaching, research, recruitment, the campus construction and annual report 2014. The meeting approved the University Board of Trustees Rules of Procedure, key position appointment, as well as the final accounts of 2013 and budget for 2014.</p>\n\n<p>The University Board of Trustees pointed out that ShanghaiTech University has made considerable progress by reforming the university structure, management, nurturing of talents, human resource system and allocation of funding and has actively explored the deep integration of education, research and innovation. The members are confident that under the support of Ministry of Education, Shanghai Municipality, and the hard work of the all faculty and staff, ShanghaiTech will make new achievements in 2014.<img alt=\"Picture - 201403061346428421_z38VaAJ.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201403061346428421_z38VaAJ.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6719\"></p>\n'),(6720,'<p>计算机视觉领域的著名学者马毅博士，于2014年3月以全职教授身份加入上海科技大学信息科学与技术学院，他将成为上海科技大学信息学院在计算机视觉研究方向上的带头人。</p>\n\n<p>马毅教授于1995获清华大学自动化学士学位和应用数学学士学位；1997年获加利福利亚大学伯克利分校电子工程与计算机科学硕士学位；2000年获加利福利亚大学伯克利分校数学硕士学位，同年获该校电子工程与计算机科学博士学位。他于2000至2006年任伊利诺伊大学厄巴拿香槟分校电子与计算机工程系助理教授；于2006至2011年任伊利诺伊大学厄巴拿香槟分校电子与计算机工程系副教授；于2009至2014年任微软研究院计算机视觉组主任及首席研究员。他曾获得1999年国际计算机视觉大会（ICCV）David Marr最佳论文奖，2004年美国自然科学基金（NSF）优秀青年学者奖CAREER Award和2005年美国海军部杰出青年学者奖Young Investigator Award；2011年获微软优秀员工金星奖Gold Star Award。他在2013年成为 IEEE Fellow。2007-2011，年他担任国际期刊《IEEE Trans. on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence》的副主编，现任《IEEE Trans. on Information Theory》、《International Journal of Computer Vision》、《IMA Journal on Information and Inference》和《SIAM Journal on Imaging Sciences》的副主编。他还曾担任国际计算机视觉大会（ICCV）的领域主席、程序委员会主席和大会主席等职，并多次应邀出席国际会议并作报告。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201405161418534052.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6721\"></p>\n'),(6722,'<p>Dr. Yi Ma, a famous scholar in computer vision, joined in the School of Information Science and Technology, ShanghaiTech University as a full-time professor who would lead the study of computer vision in March, 2014.</p>\n\n<p>Yi Ma received Bachelor’s degree in Automation and Applied Mathematics from Tsinghua University, Beijing, China, in 1995. He received a Master degree in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences (EECS) in 1997, a second Master degree in Mathematics in 2000, and the Ph.D. degree in EECS in 2000, all from the University of California at Berkeley. He served as associated professor from 2000 to 2006 and vice professor from 2006 to 2011 of the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering, University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign. From 2009 to 2014, he served as research manager for the Visual Computing Group at Microsoft Research Asia, Beijing, China. His PhD research won the David Marr Best Paper Award at the International Conference on Computer Vision (ICCV) in 1999. He was the recipient of the Faculty Early Career Development (CAREER) Award from the National Science Foundation (NSF) in 2004. He was also the recipient of the Young Investigator Program (YIP) Award from the Office of Naval Research (ONR) in 2005. He received the Gold Star Award from Microsoft Corporate in 2009. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI) from 2007 to 2011. He became a Fellow of IEEE in 2013. He has served as an associate editor of the IEEE Transactions on Pattern Analysis and Machine Intelligence (TPAMI). He currently serves as the associate editors for the IEEE Transactions on Information Theory, the International Journal of Computer Vision (IJCV), the IMA Journal on Information and Inference, and the SIAM Journal on Imaging Sciences. He also served as the Area Chair, the Program Chair and the General Chair for ICCV and was invited to present reports in many international conferences.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201405161418534052_S31shdt.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201405161418534052_S31shdt.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6723\"></p>\n'),(6724,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201408191139291671.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201408191139291671.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6725\"></p>\n\n<p>汤森路透(Thomas Reuters)于2014年6月发布了全球“高被引科学家”(Highly Cited Researchers 2014， http://highlycited.com)名单。我校信息科学和技术学院兼职（访问）教授崔曙光入选。高被引论文是根据Web of Science数据库统计，他引频次在所属领域同一年度发表的论文中排名前1%的论文。汤森路透分析了21个学科领域（横跨数学，工程，生物，农业，计算机，经济，材料，物理，化学等）2002-2012年间发表的高被引论文，将各学科领域发表高被引论文数量最多的研究人员选入全球“高被引科学家”名单。全球共有3215位研究人员入选，几乎囊括了各个领域最活跃和最有影响力的科学家。汤森路透也称此名单成员为 The world’s most influential scientific minds.</p>\n\n<p>Dr. Cui于1997年在北邮获得学士学位（系第一名），2000年在加拿大McMaster大学获得硕士学位，2005年在美国斯坦福大学获得博士学位。现在美国Texas A&amp;M大学电子与计算机工程系任副教授，并在上海科技大学任兼职（访问）教授。Dr. Cui的科研方向主要集中在：面向大数据的网络信息处理，认知无线电系统的优化和设计，无线传感器网络和物联网的能耗优化，估计与检测系统的跨层设计，基于可再生能源的通信系统优化设计。其已在国际一流期刊和会议上发表了过百篇论文，其中有八篇期刊文章自发表之日至今被引用次数在同期刊中排名前十（其中一篇引用次数排名第一，三篇引用次数排名第二)。Dr. Cui是IEEE信号处理协会2012年最佳论文奖获得者, 并曾担任多个国际期刊的编委(IEEE TSP, TWC, TVT, CL)，是IEEE通信协会无线技术委员会(WTC)的秘书长，IEEE信号处理协会SPCOM技术委员会的委员，并担任其工业／政府关系子委员会的主席。Dr. Cui在2013年当选IEEE Fellow（博士毕业后8年内当选为IEEE历史上最快之一），并在2014年被任命为IEEE Transactions on Big Data的Steering Committee委员，负责第一届主编的选定。</p>\n'),(6726,'<p>信息学院全体教职员工喜迎2014级秋季入学的新同学（含第一届本科生95名和第二届研究生87名）。同学们通过学校与学院安排的一系列迎新活动，加深了对上海科技大学的了解,坚定了对未来学习生活的信念。研究生课程已于9月9日正式开始。本科同学将在军训结束后正式开始他们期盼已久的大学生活。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6727\"></p>\n'),(6728,'<p>The faculty and staff of SIST joyfully welcome our new students coming in 2014, which include the first batch of undergraduate students and second batch of graduate students. Through substantial activities in the orientation, students got to know more about ShanghaiTech and strengthened their confidence towards future study and living here. The graduate courses have started since September 9. Undergraduate freshmen are going to set out for their long expected college education very soon after finishing their military training.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974_c84HgXy.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Orientation 20148974_c84HgXy.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6729\"></p>\n'),(6730,'<p>美国特拉华大学的虞晶怡副教授和卡内基梅陇大学的李昕副教授加盟上科大，成为信息学院的访问教授。</p>\n'),(6731,'<p>Prof. Jinyi Yu, Associate Professor at the University of Delaware, and Prof. Xin Li, Associate Professor at Carnegie Mellon University have joined the SIST as visiting professors.</p>\n'),(6732,'<p>自2014年7月以来加入信息学院的新老师有：耿艳林助理教授，袁晓军助理教授，罗喜良副教授，高盛华助理教授，师泽仁（Soeren Schwertfeger）助理教授，王浩宇助理教授，Boris Houska助理教授。此外已确定在2015年稍后上任的同事有：刘晓培助理教授，陆疌助理教授，孟子阳助理教授，王雄助理教授，张良峰助理教授，郑友怡助理教授。</p>\n'),(6733,'<p>The professors who have joined the SIST since July 2014 includes: Dr. Yanling Geng, Xiaojun Yuan, Shenghua Gao, Soeren Schwertfeger, Haoyu Wang, and Boris Houska as Assistant Professors, and Xiliang Luo as Associate Professor. In addition, 6 new colleagues include Dr. Xiaopei Liu, Dr. Jie Lu, Dr. Ziyang Meng, Dr. Xiong Wang, Dr. Liangfeng Zhang, Dr. Youyi Zheng will report on duty later in 2015.</p>\n'),(6734,'<p>2015年1月22日，信息学院在岳阳路校区举行首次务虚会议，全体教职员工出席，江绵恒校长等校领导及其他有关职能部门同事列席。在会议中，执行院长丁峙教授回顾了学院筹建至今教员招聘及发展情况，并转达了国际咨询委员会对学院未来发展的指导性建议。其后学院的学术、教学、研究生招生、学术讲座、公共关系等五个委员会对其工作进行了回顾，介绍了各自的章程，讨论了未来的工作计划。在听取了上述报告后，学院教师与校领导一起就学院各方面的发展进行了广泛的交流，并就学院的未来发展展开深入的探讨。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004245165.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6735\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004506755.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6736\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310005041729.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6737\"></p>\n'),(6738,'<p>The School of Information Science and Technology (SIST) has held their first retreat meeting in the Puxi campus at Jan. 22, 2015. All presidents of ShanghaiTech including President Mianheng Jiang, and some colleagues in other functional offices has also attended this meeting. In the meeting, Prof. Zhi Ding, the executive dean reviewed the faculty recruitment and development since establishing and summarized the guiding comments from the international advisory board. After that, the chairs of Academic Committee, Curriculum Committee, Graduate Admission Committee, Seminar Committee, and Public Relation Committee reported their achievements in 2014, introduced their drafted by-laws, and discussed their future plan. After the reports, the faculty members of SIST make an extensive communication with the university leaders regarding different issues about the school development; they have also made a brainstorm about their future roadmap.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004245165_hgmDMnB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004245165_hgmDMnB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6739\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310004506755_syJmdXe.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310004506755_syJmdXe.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6740\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201501310005041729_ZwroWNi.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201501310005041729_ZwroWNi.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6741\"></p>\n'),(6742,'<p>在加州大学伯克利分校与上海科技大学交换计划的支持下，我校信息学院向伯克利派遣了第一批师生代表。周平强助理教授、高盛华助理教授、廖凯（二年级硕士研究生），在2015年一月份到达伯克利，开始为期半年的学习、交流与研究生活。</p>\n\n<p>根据两校协议，我校交流团代表将旁听伯克利的相关课程，并将伯克利出色的课程经验移植到上科大。年轻的教授可以通过该计划与伯克利的相关老师建立长期的科研关系。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201502031733531115.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6743\"></p>\n'),(6744,'<p>Supported by the Berkeley-ShanghaiTech-Exchange (BeSTEC) Program, the first delegation of SIST@ShanghaiTech, consisting of Professor Pingqiang Zhou, Professor Shenghua Gao, and Mr. Kai Liao (2nd year graduate student), has started their Berkeley time from the last week of Jan. 2015.</p>\n\n<p>According to the program, professors and students of SIST can attend part of the Berkeley courses, which would later be offered to SIST students. This program will also help the junior faculty members at ShanghaiTech to build research connections with the faculty at Berkeley.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201502031733531115_7F2rgXp.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201502031733531115_7F2rgXp.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6745\"></p>\n'),(6746,'<p>信息学院研究生刘晓晨的论文被DAC (Design Automation Conference) 2015接收。他的论文题目是“A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation”。刘晓晨的导师是周平强教授。</p>\n\n<p>DAC是电路设计和自动化领域的顶级国际会议，每年举办一次。 今年的DAC会议将于6月份在美国旧金山召开。</p>\n'),(6747,'<p>SIST student Xiaochen Liu’s paper was accepted by Design Automation Conference (DAC) 2015. His paper is titled “A Statistical Methodology for Noise Sensor Placement and Full-Chip Voltage Map Generation”. Xiaochen’s advisor is Prof. Pingqiang Zhou.</p>\n\n<p>DAC is the premier conference for the design and automation of electronic systems. DAC 2015 will be held in San Francisco in June 2015. </p>\n'),(6748,'<p>2015年4月20日下午，信息学院学术报告讲座在我校岳阳路校区举行，斯坦福大学计算机科学系教授Leonidas Guibas带来了主题为“Networks of Shapes and Images”的报告。</p>\n\n<p>首先，信息学院执行院长马毅教授为大家介绍了Leonidas Guibas教授的学术生涯。Guibas教授是图形学方面的专家，也是美国计算机协会会士（ACM Fellow）、美国电子电气工程师协会会士（IEEE Fellow）, 获得过ACM Allen Newell奖。他的学术成果丰富，其中享誉世界的成果包括：双重散列法分析、红黑树、四边数据结构、Voronoi-Delaunay算法、EMD距离、Kinetic数据结构（KDS）、Metropolis light transport、heat-kernel signatures以及functional maps。</p>\n\n<p>Guibas教授在报告开头讲到，在科学、工程、医学和商业中，我们会面临来自各个方面的海量数据，而这些数据往往会包含几何或者视觉特征。更重要的是，我们收集到的这些几何数据集通常情况下是高度相关的。他介绍了基本的数学和计算工具，可以用来对这些相关的关系网进行建模、分析和研究。通过研究发现这些数据提供了丰富的特性。报告中，Guibas教授用了大量有趣的图片引发了师生们的强烈兴趣，报告结束后进行了广泛的交流讨论。</p>\n\n<p>【Leonidas Guibas 简介】</p>\n\n<p>       Leonidas Guibas 1976年从斯坦福大学获得博士学位，师从Donald Knuth。他之后在施乐帕克研究中心（Xerox PARC）、麻省理工学院和DEC系统研究中心（DEC SRC）工作过。从1984年开始在斯坦福大学计算机科学系任教授。他培养的博士生中，有几位已经享誉计算几何学界，例如John Hershberger、Jack Snoeyink和Jorge Stolfi，或者在计算机图形学中很有名, 例如 David Salesin、Eric Veach以及 Niloy Mitra。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201504232315256998.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6749\"></p>\n'),(6750,'<p>On April 20, 2015, Leonidas Guibas, professor of computer science at Stanford University, gave a talk named “Networks of Shapes and Images” to ShanghaiTech faculty and students.</p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yi Ma, executive dean of School of Information Science and Technology (SIST), introduced the speaker’s academic career. As an ACM Fellow, an IEEE Fellow and winner of the ACM Allen Newell Award, Prof. Guibas is a well-known master in computer graphics. Some of his well-known accomplishments include the analysis of double hashing, red-black trees, the quad-edge data structure, Voronoi-Delaunay algorithms, the Earth Mover’s distance, Kinetic Data Structures (KDS), Metropolis light transport, heat-kernel signatures and functional maps.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Guibas pointed out that, across science, engineering, medicine and business we faced a deluge of data coming from sensors, simulations or activities of individuals on the internet, and the data often contain geometric and/or visual characters. Furthermore, the geometric data sets we collected were frequently highly correlated, reflecting information about the same or similar entities, or echoing semantically important repetitions/symmetries or hierarchical structures common to both man-made and natural objects. He described general mathematical and computational tools for the construction, analysis and exploitation of such relational networks. By creating societies of data sets and their associations in a globally consistent way, we enabled a certain joint understanding of the data that provided the powers of abstraction, analogy, compression, error correction and summarization. Faculty and students were greatly attracted to the intriguing images Prof. Guibas showed during the talk, and had extensive discussion with him afterwards.</p>\n\n<p>Bio:</p>\n\n<p>Leonidas Guibas obtained his Ph.D. from Stanford in 1976, under the supervision of Donald Knuth. His subsequent employers include Xerox PARC, MIT, and DEC/SRC. He has been at Stanford since 1984 as Professor of Computer Science. He has produced several Ph.D. students who are well-known in computational geometry, such as John Hershberger, Jack Snoeyink and Jorge Stolfi, or in computer graphics, such as David Salesin, Eric Veach and Niloy Mitra.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201504232315256998_OMLDqoo.JPG\" title=\"Picture - 201504232315256998_OMLDqoo.JPG\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6751\"></p>\n'),(6752,'<p>信息学院2015年秋季学期为研究生开设了《可再生能源系统》课程。为配合该课程教学，在教务处支持下，学院组织相关的老师和同学们前往上海电气风能有限公司/西门子风力发电设备(上海)有限公司进行实地参观学习。在该公司张毅工程师的引领下，一行人聆听了风力发电的发展现状以及该公司的发展历程，参观了2.5MW / 4MW风力发电机装配车间，并且驱车到该公司在东海旁的试验风电场感受真实的风力发电。通过参观风电企业，同学们加深了对可再生能源系统以及上海本地风电产业的认识。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201505200733119750.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6753\"></p>\n'),(6754,'<p><i>Renewable Energy System</i> is a new graduate course offered in the fall semester of 2015. As a supplement to this course, the school has organized a field trip to a local sino-foreign wind power company, Shanghai Electric Wind Energy Co. Ltd / Siemens Wind Power Turbines (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. Thanks to the guidance of Yi Zhang, an engineer of the company, the visitors have listened to the state of the art of wind power industry in China, as well as the history of the company. After the introduction, they were guided to visit the assembly workshop of 2.5 MW / 4 MW wind turbines. Finally, they have a close look at the testing wind farm on the shore of East China Sea. The field trip has offered the students an immediate and memorable impression on renewable energy system and local wind power industry.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201505200733119750_1PUK7EL.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201505200733119750_1PUK7EL.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6755\"></p>\n'),(6756,'<p>5月26日上午，上海博物馆副馆长胡江和校长江绵恒来到信息学院参观3D系统展示。信息学院执行院长、教授马毅陪同参观展示。</p>\n\n<p>在3D系统展示的过程中，教授虞晶怡详细介绍了3D系统的采集、传输、显示各个部分的详细情况，其中摄像头阵列能够实时采集显示3D场景令人印象深刻。随后双方探讨了在博物馆应用3D系统的可能性。江绵恒指出，实现科技与产业的结合是上科大的核心办学理念之一，希望学院与上博积极探讨，把握住这次很好的产学研合作机会。</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20150609133045145.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6757\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331003762.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6758\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331137173.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6759\"></p>\n'),(6769,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6770,'<p>On May 26th, Deputy director of Shanghai Museum Dr. Hu Jiang and President Jiang Mianheng, accompanied by Professor Ma Yi, executive dean of SIST, visited the 3D Imaging Lab housed at SIST.</p>\n\n<p>Prof. Yu Jingyi demonstrated a novel 3D imaging system to the visitors and gave an in-depth presentation on its acquisition, data transmission and display modules. Of particular interest is the portable camera array that enables naked-eye 3D viewing. All visitors were impressed by the demonstration. After that, the two parties have further discussed potential collaborations on applying the 3D imaging system for a broad range of applications at Shanghai Museum. President Jiang Mianheng pointed out that, integrating research and real-life application is central to the mission of ShanghaiTech and SIST. He hopes that discussions today will lead to concrete collaboration between ShanghaiTech and Shanghai Museum in the near future.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 20150609133045145_qMff62E.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 20150609133045145_qMff62E.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6771\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331003762_2ZwmfSB.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331003762_2ZwmfSB.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6772\"></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Picture - 201506091331137173_P1lWPJ6.jpg\" title=\"Picture - 201506091331137173_P1lWPJ6.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6773\"></p>\n'),(6782,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6783,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6784,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6788,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Examining the Landscape and Impact of Android Application Plagiarism.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6789\"></p>\n'),(6793,'<p>Enter your Content</p>'),(6797,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - A Brief Introduction to IC Design and EDA.jpg\" title=\"Picture - A Brief Introduction to IC Design and EDA.jpg\" src=\"/static/cms/img/icons/plugins/image.png\" id=\"plugin_obj_6798\"></p>\n'),(6804,'<p><img alt=\"Picture - Classifying Computational Couning Problems.jpg\" title=\"Picture - Classifying Computationa